<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali Leaders Express Condolences over Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, February 20 (Xinhua) -- King of Nepal Birendra today
expressed his grief over the demise of Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping, who died Wednesday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
In a condolence message sent to Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
the king said that Deng will be remembered long as the architect
of modern China who successfully guided China's modernization
efforts.
</P>
<P>
"We recall his visit to Nepal in 1978 and his contribution to
strengthening Nepal-China relations," the king said, adding that
in Deng's demise China has lost a great leader and Nepal a friend
and well-wisher.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Nepali Prime Minister Sher Bahadur Deuba today also
sent a condolence message to his Chinese counterpart Li Peng to
express his sorrow over the death of Deng.
</P>
<P>
While mourning over Deng's death, President of the main ruling
Nepali Congress (NC) party Girija Prasad Koirala in his condolence
message to Li Peng said that Deng has played a crucial role in the
economic transformation in China.
</P>
<P>
Nepal's main opposition the Communist Party of Nepal (United
Marxist Leninist) today adjourned its on-going Standing Central
Committee Meeting on hearing the news of Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
The CPN-UML said in a statement today that as an extraordinary
leader, Deng has made contribution to enabling China to reach the
pinnacle of socialist modernization, introducing China to the
world as an able, strong, modern and socialist country, and
leading the Chinese people towards a brighter 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The demise of Deng is a big loss not only to the Communist
Party, the people and the government of China but also to the
people all over the world, the statement said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
