<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU's Jacques Santer Speaks Highly of Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 20 (Xinhua) -- The top official of the
European Union (EU) said today "the mark Deng Xiaoping has made on
the 20th century shall be remembered by the whole world well into
the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
Jacques Santer, President of the European Commission, the
executive arm of the 15-member EU, made the remarks in a statement
following the death of the Chinese leader on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Deng's leadership had made an immense contribution to
modernization and economic reform in China, and to opening up the
country to the rest of the world, Santer said.
</P>
<P>
"He has set in train a process of market reform which has now
become irreversible," he said. "This has enabled Europe and China
to build up a flourishing relationship in trade and investment and
to begin the process of deeper political ties."
</P>
<P>
Santer also expressed his confidence that Deng's legacy will
"benefit not only all the people of China but their partners in
the region and in the wider world." 
</P>
</TEXT>
