<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anson Chan Welcomes Tung's List of HKSAR Principal Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Chief Secretary
Anson Chan welcomed here tonight the list of 23 principal
officials of the first government of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), which was just released by Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa.
</P>
<P>
The Central People's Government has announced the appointment
of all eligible serving officers as principle officials of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, in other words, Tung's
nominations have been accepted by the government, she said.
</P>
<P>
"I personally am very encouraged by this news. As you know,
these officials have been my colleagues for many, many years and I
have every confidence in their ability and their loyalty to Hong
Kong," said Chan, who will stay to assume the office of the
Administrative Secretary of the first HKSAR government.
</P>
<P>
Their appointment as principal officials will ensure the
continuity of top civil service during the transition period, Chan
noted.
</P>
<P>
She believed that the move will be welcomed both by the civil
service and by the entire community.
</P>
<P>
She also, on behalf of her colleagues, congratulated Elsie
Leung Oi-sie on her appointment as Secretary of Justice and Lily
Yam Kwan Pui-ying on her appointment as Commissioner Against
Corruption, and extended welcome to them.
</P>
<P>
Leung, a renowned solicitor, said she is deeply delighted to
join the civil service of HKSAR and to be appointed to the post.
</P>
<P>
"It is a great honor to be one of them and to be the first
Secretary of Justice -- the first Chinese Secretary of Justice of
the HKSAR," she said.
</P>
<P>
It is important for the Secretary of Justice to uphold the
Basic Law and to maintain the present legal system and bear the
interests of six million Hong Kong people in mind, she added.
</P>
<P>
Also meeting with the press was Yam, who will be the first
Commissioner Against Corruption of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
She called her appointment to the post "both an honor and a
challenge".
</P>
<P>
"I will do my utmost to discharge the responsibilities of the
Commissioner Against Corruption," she said. Yam served in the
Independent Commission Against Corruption (ICAC) for nine years
and now is Commissioner for Transport in the Hong Kong government.
</P>
<P>
She praised ICAC staff as dedicated and having high morale,
saying the future Commission Against Corruption of HKSAR will
combat corruption efficiently with the support of the staff and
the community at large.
</P>
<P>
The list of HKSAR principal officials, which Tung Chee Hwa
revealed tonight after returning from Beijing, retains nearly the
whole team of the incumbent government secretaries, except
Attorney-General Jeremy Mathews, who is not a Chinese citizen, and
Commissioner of ICAC Michael Leung Man-kin, who offered to retire.
</P>
</TEXT>
