<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Leaders Condole Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga, Prime Minister Sirimavo Bandaranaike sent their
respective condolence letters today to Chinese Leaders over the
death of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
In her letter to Chinese President Jiang Zemin, the president
said, "My government and I have been deeply saddened by the news
of the passing away of China's paramount leader Deng Xiaoping."
</P>
<P>
She said the late leader's achievement, as the architect of the
program of economic reform and modernization, in propelling China
along a path of rapid development, has earned universal admiration
and acclaim.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that his inspirational leadership will enable
those who follow him at the helm of China's affairs to realize the
goals he set for his country," the president said.
</P>
<P>
she said, "The late Deng Xiaoping manifested a cordial and
abiding friendship for Sri Lanka, and we all deeply mourn his
passing."
</P>
<P>
The president pointed out, "Our sincere good wishes go out too,
to the people of China, as they embark on a further stage of
progress along the path chartered by their paramount leader."
</P>
<P>
In her letter to Chinese Premier Li Peng, Prime Minister
Sirimavo said, Deng Xiaoping's demise "is not only an
irreplaceable loss to China but also to friends of China including
Sri Lanka."
</P>
<P>
She noted that the late statesman Deng Xiaoping will be long
remembered for his vision and leadership in laying the foundation
for modern China through dynamic economic reforms.  
</P>
</TEXT>
