<HEADLINE> Kim Jong Il Mourns Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYNOGYANG, February 20 (Xinhua) -- The top leader of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) today expressed
condolences on the death of the Chinese leader of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Kim Jong Il, Chairman of the National Defense Commission of the
DPRK and Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army, praised
Deng in a telegram addressed to Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
The message, Kim said, was sent on behalf of his nation and its
people.
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping had made historic contributions to the Communist
Party of China and the Chinese revolution up to the last moment of
his life since he embarked upon the road of the revolution in his
early years," he said.
</P>
<P>
Calling him an intimate friend of the Korean people, Kim
recalled the friendship between Deng and his father, Kim Il Sung,
the late leader of DPRK, and hailed Deng's efforts to strengthen
and develop the traditional friendship between China and his
country.
</P>
<P>
"His death is a great loss not only to the Chinese party and
people but also to the Korean people," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
