<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Car Output Down 1 Percent in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 20 (Xinhua) -- German automotive production
reduced by one percent in January to 394,000 units, the
Frankfurt-based German Automobile Industry Association (VDA)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Last month saw a 9 percent increase in export orders, but also
a 9 percent decline in domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
The VDA said that private cars and vans accounted for 366,700
of the total output, down 2 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
A severe plunge of 28 percent in production of heavy-duty
commercial vehicles occurred, according to the VDA, which blamed
this on economic downturn and in particular, the slowdown in the
building sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
