<HEADLINE> Pak President Condemns Terrorist Act in Multan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's President Farooq
Leghari today strongly condemned the act of terrorism in Multan,
Punjab, in which an Iranian official and six Pakistani people were
killed.
</P>
<P>
Leghari directed the governor of Punjab province to take prompt
action to apprehend the culprits so that stern action could be
taken against them for this heinous crime.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani president has sent a message of condolence to
Iranian President Rafsanjani on the demise of Agha Muhammad Ali
Rahimee, director of the Iranian Cultural Center.
</P>
<P>
He also sympathized with bereaved families of six Pakistani
nationals who were killed during the firing incident.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan, six
attackers armed with automatic weapons this afternoon forced their
entry into the Iranian Cultural Center in Multan and started
indiscriminate firing.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen fled quickly after the killing before the local
police and officials rushed to the scene.
</P>
<P>
So far no groups have claimed responsibility for the incident.
Investigations are still under way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
