<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Maldivian President Condoles Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Maldivian President Maumoon
Abdul Gayoom today expressed his grief at the passing away of
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
In his condolence massage to Chinese President Jiang Zemin, he
said, "It was with deep regret and sorrow that I learned of the
passing away of China's great national leader Deng Xiaoping. This
is indeed a great loss for the government of China and for the
entire Chinese people."
</P>
<P>
He said Deng Xiaoping was a great statesman whose pragmatic and
 enlightened leadership enabled China to modernize its economy and
achieve economic growth and social progress.
</P>
<P>
The president said that at this time of profound national grief
and mourning, "the government and the people of the Republic of
Maldives  join me in expressing our sincere condolences to your
excellency and the government and people of China and in
particular, to the members of the bereaved family."  
</P>
</TEXT>
