<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host C'Wealth Forestry Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe will in May host the
15th Commonwealth Forestry Conference (CFC) whose recommendations
will form the basis of the Commonwealth Heads of Government
Meeting (CHOGM) on forest management policies.
</P>
<P>
The conference, coming at a time when most of the world had
put in place some projects to reverse rapid deforestation, seeks
to foster cooperation in the fields of research, education and
training.
</P>
<P>
''The 15th CFC, which is being organized by the Forestry
Commission, will deliberate on three sub-topics, namely the
interface between the community, the state and the private
sector, the technological means of ensuring sustainable forestry,
and the products and services of forestry,'' a statement from
Zimbabwe's Forestry Commission said today.
</P>
<P>
The Forestry Commission said some 400 delegates representing
government, industry, private sector and academics are expected
to attend the week-long conference, which begins on May 12 in the
northern resort town of Victoria Falls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
