<HEADLINE> EU GDP Up by 0.81 Percent in Third Quarter 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 20 (Xinhua) -- There was a spurt of 0.81
percent in real Europan Union GDP(Gross Domestic Product) in third
quarter last year, EU's statistical office Eurostat estimated
today.
</P>
<P>
This growth compares with rises of 0.46 percent in both first
and second quarters last year.
</P>
<P>
This latest quarterly growth came mainly from private
consumption(up 0.74 percent) and exports, which rose 2.23 percent,
Eurostat commented.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat reported that among the 15 EU member states, Germany
and particularly Finland showed strong Q3 growth of 1.14 percent
aent and 0.39 percent.
</P>
<P>
Growth in Denmark(0.99 percent), and United Kingdom(0.45
percent) and the Netherlands(0.60 percent) was lower than in the
second quarter.
</P>
<P>
Private consumption growth was highest in Sweden(1.81 percent),
Denmark(1.31 percent), the UK(0.99 percent) and France(0.91
percent).
</P>
<P>
Exports rose by 3.47 percent in Germany and 3.11 percent in
France.  
</P>
</TEXT>
