<HEADLINE> Cambodian Second PM Speaks Highly of Deng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen said today the death of Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping on Wednesday is a great loss in Chinese and world history.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to the Chinese Embassy here, Hun Sen laid
wreath over the picture of Deng and handed over his message of
condolences addressed to Chinese Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
In the message, to be delivered through Xie Yue, the Chinese
Ambassador to Cambodia, the Cambodian leader described Deng as "a
distinguished son and an able leader of the Chinese nation."
</P>
<P>
His death, Hun Sen said, "is one of the great losses in Chinese
and world history" because of his achievements, including the
contribution to regional and world peace, security, stability and
development. 
</P>
