<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SADC Quality Conference to Be Held in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 20 (Xinhua) -- A total quality management
conference to sustain and improve quality management systems in
the region will be held in Harare next month, the Zimbabwe News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The conference, to be held from March 20 to 21, is a follow-up
to the Southern African Development Community (SADC) meeting held
last November in Harare, under which it seemed that there was
increasing awareness about quality within the region.
</P>
<P>
Next month's conference is aimed at exposing the delegates to
international trends in total quality management and
environmental management.
</P>
<P>
Issues to be resolved would include identifying key success
factors for maintaining a leading edge on the international
markets, defining the relationship between quality management
(iso 9000), environmental management (iso 1400) and total quality
management and business excellence, and what needs to be done to
move from an iso 9000 to an integrated management system.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
