<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece's Current Accounts Deficit Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Greece's current accounts
deficit in January-October 1996 rose to 4.3 billion U.S. dollars,
compared to 3 billion dollars in the corresponding ten-month
period of 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released today by the Bank of Greece, the
increase was due to a 952.4 million dollar widening of the trade
deficit coupled with a 302.8 million dollar reduction in the
invisibles surplus.
</P>
<P>
In October 1996, the current accounts deficit reached 646
million dollars, compared to 627 million dollars in the same month
of 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
