<HEADLINE> Ruggiero Nominates Three Panelists on Helms-Burton Act </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, February 20 (Xinhua) -- World Trade Organization (WTO)
Director-General Renato Ruggiero today named three panelists for a
dispute between the United States and the European Union (EU) over
the U.S. anti-Cuba Helms-Burton law.
</P>
<P>
The chairman of the panel, its establishment announced on
November 20, 1996 at EU's request, is Arthur Dunkel, a Swiss
professor of economics.
</P>
