<HEADLINE> Italian FM Sent Condolence Message on Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini said the death of Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping had deprived
China of "the father of its great economic reforms" and the world
of "one of the most prominent personalities of the century."
</P>
<P>
In a letter of condolences, Dini asked his Chinese counterpart,
Qian Qichen, to "accept the most sincere and keenly-felt
condolences with which I partake of the mourning of the Chinese
people."
</P>
<P>
Dini noted that the Chinese people were linked to the Italian
people "by happy bonds of cooperation and friendship."
</P>
<P>
In Deng's death on Wednesday, "your country lost the father of
its great economic reforms and the policy of opening China to the
outside world... while the world has lost one of the most
prominent personalities of the century," Dini said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
