<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Agency to Purchase Food From Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 20 (Xinhua) -- The World Food Program
(WFP) said today it is arranging to purchase and export 6,000
tons of food crop from Ethiopia in aid to Kenya and Uganda.
</P>
<P>
WFP country director Khaled Adley told local journalists here
that his organization is preparing to purchase 4,000 tons of
maize and 2,000 tons of pulses from Ethiopia to export food aid
to Uganda and Kenya.
</P>
<P>
''This is an initial quantity and we may continue on larger
scale,'' he said, adding that WFP is also planning to purchase up
to 100,000 tons of food grain from Ethiopia for its operations
within Ethiopia itself.
</P>
<P>
Adley added that purchasing of food grain from surplus
producing areas to deliver them to regions in need of food
through the WFP is expected to benefit about 1.2 million people
in Ethiopia this year.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has 600,000 tons of surplus grain this year after
harvesting 11.7 million tons of crop in the last agricultural
season, 2 million tons more than the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
