<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Personages Mourn Deng's Death (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wan Guoquan, He Luli and Cai Zimin shared the view that the
Chinese Patriotic United Front is now experiencing unprecedented
unity, thanks to the theories, principles and policies for the
group that were put forward by Deng.
</P>
<P>
Wan is vice-chairman of CPPCC National Committee and
vice-chairman of China Democratic National Construction
Association (CDNCA) Central Committee. He Luli, also vice-chairman
of the CPPCC National Committee, is the chairman of the
Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomingtang (RCCK) Central
Committee. Cai is the Presidium of the Central Committee of the
Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League.
</P>
<P>
They said that Deng's creation of the principle of "one
country, two systems," viewed as a pioneering philosophy by the
world community, has cleared the way for a bright future for the
peaceful reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Vice-chairman of NPC Standing Committee and honorary chairman
of All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce (ACFIC) Wang
Guangying, Vice-chairman of NPC Standing Committee and ACFIC
honorary chairman Sun Fuling, and ACFIC chairman Jing Shuping
recalled the kind attention and guidance Deng gave to former
industrialists and businessmen.
</P>
<P>
They said that Deng met with several industrial and commercial
leaders soon after the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC Central
Committee, and pointed out that the role of former industrialists
and businessmen should be given full play in the construction of
socialist modernization, to show clearly in which direction the
ACFIC should go.
</P>
<P>
Since the reform and opening to the outside world, an economic
structure based on public ownership and supplemented with
multi-ownerships has formed in China. The healthy development of
non-public ownership has contributed to the economic growth and
social progress.
</P>
<P>
"That cannot be separated from the principles and policies made
by Deng Xiaoping," they said.
</P>
<P>
The non-Communist persons said that though Deng has died, he
will live forever in their hearts. The blueprint he designed for
the country's reform and opening is being carried out step by step
by people all over the country who are led by the CPC Central
Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
"We should turn grief into strength, and unite more closely
around the CPC Central Committee with Jiang at the core, so as to
contribute more to the construction of socialist modernization and
reunification of the motherland," they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
