<HEADLINE> Hong Kong People Mourn Deng's Death (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 20 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,000 Hong Kong
citizens went to the mourning hall at the Xinhua News Agency Hong
Kong Branch this afternoon to offer their condolences to Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping, who passed away Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Inside the mourning hall hung a photograph of the deceased
along with a banner inscribed with "Esteemed Deng Xiaoping is
immortal". Wreaths were placed in front of the photo and around
the hall.
</P>
<P>
After three o'clock this afternoon, the grief-loaded mourners
moved in batches into the hall to pay their last respect to the
great man. Some could not help crying for the loss of the chief
architect of China's reform and opening-up and modernization
drive. It is estimated that some 2,000 people paid their tributes
to Deng within two hours.
</P>
<P>
Ann Tse-kai and Henry Fok Ying-tong, both vice chairmen of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
National Committee, Zhou Nan, director of the Xinhua News Agency
Hong Kong Branch, Tung Chee Hwa, the first Chief Executive of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), Rita Fan Hsu Lai
Tai, president of the HKSAR Provisional Legislative Council (PLC),
members of the HKSAR first Executive Council, and PLC members,
representatives of various social groups and many Hong Kong
dignitaries including film magnate Run Run Shaw and properties
tycoon Li Ka-shing all came mourning the death of the esteemed
Deng.
</P>
<P>
Ann Tse-kai recalled his meeting with Deng several years ago in
 Beijing. He said: "The concept of 'one country, two systems'
and 'Hong Kong people ruling Hong Kong' is a pioneering
undertaking. It is a pity that Deng could not see with his own
eyes the moment Hong Kong returns to China."
</P>
<P>
Henry Fok Ying-tong felt deeply grieved about Deng's death. He
described Deng as a great leader of the Chinese people, who not
only chartered the course of reform and opening-up, but also put
forward the creative concept of "one country, two systems" to
successfully resolve the Hong Kong issue.
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan, the PLC president, expressed her wishes to fulfill
the obligations of the PLC step by step, so as to fully implement
the concept of "one country, two systems", devised by Deng.
</P>
</TEXT>
