<HEADLINE> Heavy Storm Sweeps Germany, Killing at Least One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 20 (Xinhua) -- A heavy storm with winds of up to
100 kilometers an hour swept northern and central Germany on
Wednesday evening and this morning, killing at least one person.
</P>
<P>
The only death so far confirmed occurred in a road accident
caused by the storm. The man, whose name was withheld by police,
was killed when road signs were blown onto the highway.
</P>
<P>
While no other major damage has been reported to authorities,
two seagoing vessels came into a slight collision on the canal
linking the Baltic Sea and the North Sea.
</P>
<P>
In addition, trees were uprooted in the state of Hesse, and
heavy snowfall disrupted traffic in northern Bavaria and Thuringia.
</P>
<P>
Other states witnessed heavy thunder-squalls and hail showers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, reports reaching here said the ongoing storm
attacking western and central Europe has caused five deaths in
Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
