<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People Mourn Deng Xiaoping (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese people today were
saddened to hear the news of the passing of their former leader
Deng Xiaoping, who died Wednesday night in Beijing at the age of
93.
</P>
<P>
Early this morning, the Communist Party of China (CPC)'s
Central Committee, the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress, the State Council, the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, and the Central
Military Commission jointly published a letter to the whole Party,
the whole army, and the people of various ethnic groups throughout
the country announcing Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
The news soon spread across cities, villages, pastures,
government institutions, factories and mines, and schools, and
threw the entire nation into a state of mourning.
</P>
<P>
People of various ethnic groups across the country vowed to
turn grief into strength, carry on Deng's unfinished cause, and
continue to work hard for the great undertaking of reform, opening
up, and socialist modernization under the leadership of the Party
Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
Various departments and institutions directly under the CPC
Central Committee today eulogized Deng by reviewing his glorious
revolutionary career and great contributions to the country, while
all officials and employees of the central government departments
pledged to inherit Deng's legacy by continuing to build socialism
with Chinese characteristics and performing their duties more
conscientiously.
</P>
<P>
Legislators attending a meeting of the Eighth NPC Standing
Committee, which opened yesterday in Beijing, observed three
minutes of silence before beginning today's discussions.
</P>
<P>
Staff workers of the NPC also convened a meeting to mourn Deng,
and said they will work diligently to prepare for the upcoming
Fifth Session of the Eighth NPC National Congress, which will open
on March 1.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0052 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People Mourn Deng Xiaoping (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents in the coastal provinces and municipalities at the
forefront of the opening up, such as Liaoning Province, Shanghai
and Guangdong Province along the east coast, have expressed their
shock over the news.
</P>
<P>
"Deng contributed so much to the country that without him, it
is unlikely we would be living so well," said a taxi-driver in the
capital of north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
In the country's largest city, Shanghai, which Deng inspected
several times, many residents were in tears.
</P>
<P>
"He inspected our store on the night of the Lantern Festival in
1992, and shook hands with me. I will never forget the
experience," said Ma Guining, a shop assistant at one of the
biggest stores on Nanjing Road in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
"The festival is approaching. However, he passed away,..." she
added, crying.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Zhihao, director of the construction of Shanghai's two
newly-built bridges, Nanpu and Yangpu, said that he will remember
Deng's three inspection tours to the construction sites of the
bridges.
</P>
<P>
In south China's booming city of Shenzhen, one of the country's
five special economic zones, many people placed flowers near the
portrait of Deng.
</P>
<P>
In south China's Hainan Province, many pedestrians in the
capital city of Haikou wore black suits and white flowers to
symbolize their respect for Deng.
</P>
<P>
"We workers at the forefront of the reform love Deng because
the policies he drafted have benefitted us," said Feng Xiuzheng, a
53-year-old worker in Haikou who said she cherishes his memory.
</P>
<P>
People in many other provinces such as Hunan, Gansu and Guizhou
in central, northwest and southwest China also expressed their
sorrow.
</P>
<P>
Yan Hongchang, a deputy to the Provincial People's Congress of
east China's Anhui Province, said that the current good situation
in the country's rural areas should be attributed to Deng.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0053 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People Mourn Deng Xiaoping (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Supreme People's Court issued a circular calling for strict
law enforcement and safeguarding social stability. The Supreme
People's Procuratorate called a meeting to mourn the death of
Deng, asking procuratorates at various levels to stick to the path
of reform, development and stability.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, officials recalled Deng's great deeds as well as his
revolutionary spirit.
</P>
<P>
The All-China Federation of Trade Unions, the Central Committee
of the Communist Youth League of China, The All-China Women's
Federation and other non-governmental organizations have been also
mourning Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the
State Council, The Taiwan Work Office of the Chinese Communist
Party Central Committee, and the Taiwan Affairs Office of the
State Council expressed their sorrow.
</P>
<P>
They said that Deng died just little over 100 days before the
return of Hong Kong to the motherland. "We must mourn Deng by
working hard," they vowed.
</P>
<P>
Today, China's national flags were flown at half staff at
Tiananmen, Xinhuamen, the Great Hall of the People and the Foreign
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting held by the Beijing Municipal People's Congress,
deputies stood and observed three minutes of silence.
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Deng Xiaoping's contributions to the Chinese
revolution and construction were invaluable," said Tao Xiping,
from the congress, adding that Deng's words and deeds will have
great influence on China's future.
</P>
<P>
When the news of Deng's death reached old revolutionary regions
where Deng had fought and worked, including Guangxi, Jiangxi, and
Shanxi, the public were deeply saddened.
</P>
<P>
Li Xianxian, 86, an old Red Army soldier who took part in the
Baise Uprising led by Deng, was choked with tears as he stood in
front of Deng's picture.
</P>
<P>
In Jiangxi Province, people came to a factory where Deng worked
when he was fired during the chaotic Cultural Revolution
(1966-76), to mourn the late leader.
</P>
<P>
"Deng worked here with us for three years," said Tao Duanjin, a
worker. "His optimism and will-power impressed me most."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0054 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People Mourn Deng Xiaoping (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At six a.m., along Qingnian Road outside the Potala Palace in
Tibet, funeral music was heard coming from the television sets of
local residents watching for news of Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
In Jiari Village in Gonggar County, a farmer named Baiba who
makes handcrafts for a living, cried when he heard the
announcement. He placed a hada -- a memorial cloth -- above a
photograph of Deng, lit a lamp, made an offering of tea and prayed.
</P>
<P>
"Farmers can't forget Deng Xiaoping after they get rich," he
said.
</P>
<P>
In Urumqi, capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region, people from different nationalities gathered to
remember Deng's accomplishments.
</P>
<P>
Ahbuhan, director of the department of communications in Altay,
a city in the northernmost part of the region, was teary-eyed,
saying he was impressed with the great changes that were evident
in China after the reform and opening policies designed by Deng
were adopted.
</P>
<P>
"We Kazak people will remember his great contribution in our
hearts," he said.
</P>
<P>
In west China's Qinghai Province, many people bought newspapers
carrying the official word of Deng's death. Agya, the living
Buddha of the prestigious Tar Monastery, said that policies of
religious freedom have been carried out since the Third Plenum of
the 11th CPC Central Committee, thanks to the guidance of Deng's
ideas on the construction of socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
And in Deng's hometown of Guangan in Sichuan Province, four
million locals also felt the shock of his death. Almost all units
and neighborhood committees in the county held mourning services
today.
</P>
<P>
At about 11 a.m., many people visited Deng's former residence,
where funeral music was playing and trees were draped in white.
</P>
</TEXT>
