<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia's Media Outlet Praises Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's Tanjug News
Agency Wednesday issued a commentary highly praising the
achievements of late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
The commentary described Deng, who died Wednesday, as the
father of China's reforms and opening up to the outside world, and
a historic figure be be remembered by people around the world.
</P>
<P>
Hailing Deng's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics as a practice of combining Marxism with the real
situation in China, the commentary said the theory revitalized
socialism for the world.
</P>
<P>
With pragmatic policies and great visions, Deng led the
People's Republic through its worst period since its founding and
resuscitated the nation from its paralyzed state resulting from
the Cultural Revolution, it said.
</P>
<P>
As a result of Deng's polices, China commenced the "real and
bold" process of reforms and opening up to the outside world 19
years ago, the article said. 
</P>
