<HEADLINE> Civilian Killed in Israeli Bombardment in S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 20 (Xinhua) -- One civilian was killed in
Israeli bombardment in south Lebanon this afternoon, at a time
when a cease-fire monitoring committee is discusing a Lebanese
complaint against the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
Israeli artillery has hit at suspected guerrilla targets in
south Lebanon since this morning, following a clash between
Lebanese guerrillas and an Israeli patrol in the Israeli
self-proclaimed "security zone."
</P>
<P>
Police sources in south Lebanon said that the Israeli
occupation forces concentrated the bombardment on the areas of
Iglim Al-Toffah and Nabatiyeh.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that the Israeli artillery, at the
position of Zaffata, fired at vicinities of the south Lebanese
villages of Froum, Khandurieyh, Zautar Gharbieh and Zautar
Sharqieh in Nabatiyeh, some 75 kilometers southeast of Beirut.
</P>
<P>
A shepherd identified as Khodraj Hadi, 25, from the village of
Froum was killed by a shell around 14:30 p.m. (12:30 GMT) when he
was herding goats and sheep near Froum, according to the
sources.
</P>
<P>
The incident happened when a five-nation group monitoring a
cease-fire between Lebanon and Israel is holding a meeting in
the south Lebanese border town of Naqoura to discuss a Lebanese
complaint over the killing of a Lebanese woman in Israeli
bombardment Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Naeemeh Hallal, 33, was the first Lebanese civilian killed by
Israeli forces this year.
</P>
<P>
The cease-fire monitoring committee, comprising
representatives of France, Israel, Lebanon, Syria and the United
States, was set up under the April 1996 understanding, which
bars belligerent parties in south Lebanon from targeting
civilians.
</P>
<P>
The group started the meeting in the headquarters of the
U.N. peacekeeping forces Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the pro-Syrian Amal Movement of
Lebanon announced that its guerrillas ambushed this morning an
Israeli patrol in the central sector of the border strip,
killing and wounding several Israeli soldiers. But there was no
confirmation from the Israeli side.
</P>
<P>
Amal, headed by Lebanese House Speaker Nabih Berri, said in a
statement that the guerrillas detonated a series of bombs at
4:15 a.m. (02:15 GMT) when an Israeli Merkava tank carrying a
number of infantrymen arrived at the site of ambush.
</P>
<P>
Guerrillas of the pro-Iranian Hezbollah, or Party of God,
also said that they launched an attack at a position of the
Israeli-backed SLA militia at Tomat Niha in the border strip
this morning.
</P>
<P>
Hit-and-run attacks by Lebanese Muslim guerrillas and
bombardments by Israeli forces constitute a daily scene in south
Lebanon, the last active battlefront of the Arab-Israeli
conflict.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese guerrillas have killed one Israeli soldier and
wounded 22 others since this year.
</P>
<P>
Israel established the 1,100-square-kilometer buffer strip in
1985 in a bid to protect northern Israel from cross-border
attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
