<HEADLINE> Nigeria Sees Prices Down in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria registered a two
percent drop in consumer prices in December, leaving a lower
price hike rate in 1996 than in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The data released today by Federal Office of Statistics (FOS)
showed that the composite consumer price index in the western
African country stood at 2,668.6 in December, compared with
2,722.7 in November.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, urban and rural indices fell by 1.2 percent and 2.1
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The decline is largely due to the fall of prices of food and
materials for housing repair, FOS said.
</P>
<P>
Between December 1995 and December 1996, the nation's average
consumer price level rose by 14.3 percent, according to FOS
data. enditem

