officials of Zaire, the three ministers also reiterated African
leaders' commitment to preserving territorial integrity of Zaire
and finding peaceful solutions to the Great Lakes crisis.
</P>
<P>
The peace mission delegation, also including foreign ministers
of Zimbabwe, Cameroun and Congo, and representatives of the
Organization of African Unity, met Zaire's prime minister, deputy
prime minister, ministers of foreign affairs, defense and
interior.
</P>
<P>
The Zairean government said after a withdrawal of foreign
forces, they would settle their own problems through democratic
process, according to the press conference.
</P>
<P>
Musyoka, Nzo and Kikwete left here for Kinshasa on the peace
mission on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Zairean warring sides are holding talks in Cape
Town, South Africa. Representatives of Zairean rebel leader Laurent
Kabila and President Mobutu Sese Seko are examining peace
proposals to end the civil war. Details are not available yet.
</P>
