<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 20 (Xinhua) -- High tech companies from Hong
Kong and Taiwan announced a 26 million US dollar UK joint venture
to produce recordable compact discs (CD-Rs) and digital versatile
discs (DVDs) in Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture which comprises Hang Kong's Hanny Holdings
and Ritek of Taiwan will begin to produce CD-Rs within a few
months and DVDs in the second year, according to an official press
note released here today.
