<P>
Suitable players for DVDs are expected to appear in the
international marketplace later this year, the press note added.
</P>
<P>
Hanny's executive director Ken Cheung said, "This Northern
Ireland operation will be an integral part of a global initiative
by Hanny and Ritek to establish a leading position in the CD-R and
DVD markets."
</P>
<P>
Hanny Holdings, part owned by the giant conglomerate Hutchinson
Whampoa, employs more than 2,000 people worldwide in manufacturing
media products, while Ritek is currently Taiwan's leading
manufacturer of CDs.
</P>
<P>
They already have another joint venture in the United States.
