<HEADLINE> Iran Protests Against Killing of Its Diplomat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 20 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian government today
lodged a protest to Pakistani ambassador in Tehran against the
assassination of an Iranian diplomat in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the Iranian
Foreign Ministry summoned Pakistani Ambassador Khaled Mahmoud
and lodged a protest against the Pakistani security authorities
for failing to protect the Iranian establishments there.
</P>
<P>
Alaeddin Bourujerdi, Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister for
Asia-Pacific Affairs, strongly condemned the attack on the
Iranian Cultural Center in Multan in central Pakistan. He told
the ambassador that Iran expects the Pakistani government to
take immediate steps to bring to justice the perpetrators of the
savage act.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Mohammad Ali Rahimi, attache of
Iran's cultural center in the Pakistani province of Punjab, was
killed by an anti-Iranian group Sipah-i-Sahaba (SSP) this morning
along with four other local employees under his command.
</P>
<P>
Some 10 armed members of the SSP were said to have taken part
in the attack. However, the report said that none of the
attackers were arrested.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said the tragedy was a shocking incident for
Pakistan and its government.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Pakistani government has given assurances
that it would spare no efforts to arrest the criminals and bring
them to justice. 
</P>
