<HEADLINE> Glenn Not to Seek Fifth Term in Senate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 20 (Xinhua) -- John Glenn, the first
American in orbit, announced today that he would not seek a fifth
term in the U.S. Senate, the Associated Press said.
</P>
<P>
"Although my health remains excellent... another term in the
senate would take me at the end of that term to the age of 83,"
the 75-year-old Democrat told supporters and students at a college
chapel in New Concord, Ohio, where he grew up.
</P>
<P>
"For that reason and for that reason alone... I have decided I
will not be a candidate for re-election to the senate," Glenn
added.
</P>
<P>
Glenn, who circled the globe three times on February 20, 1962,
was elected to the Senate in 1974 on a wave of popularity that
followed his historic space mission and has served four
consecutive six-year terms. 
</P>
