hopes to promote comprehensive relations with Israel, especially
in trade and economic fields.
</P>
<P>
China and Israel established full diplomatic ties in 1992,
and the bilateral relations have developed smoothly in the past
years. Bilateral trade between the two sides amounted to 240
million U.S. dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Li Lanqing conveyed a message of good wishes
from Chinese Premier Li Peng to Netanyahu, who in reply asked
the vice-premier to send his regards to Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
During his trip, Li also held separate talks with Israeli
Foreign Minister David Levy, President Ezer Weizman, and Trade
and Industry Minister Natan Sharansky.
</P>
<P>
Li Lanqing concluded today his five-day visit which began
Sunday. 
