<HEADLINE> HK Properties Tycoon Mourns Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 21 (Xinhua) -- "I'm much grieved at hearing
Deng's death. Although it had been talked for a certain period
that his health was not so good, the news still took me by
surprise," Hong Kong property tycoon Li Ka-shing told Xinhua
today.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping died Wednesday night in Beijing at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
To the 1.2 billion Chinese people, Deng was "a very great
man," Li said with deep sorrow.
</P>
<P>
Recalling his many meetings with Deng, the head of Cheung Kong
(Holdings) Ltd. spoke highly of Deng's great contributions.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the esteemed leader had creativity and
far-sightedness on many issues.
</P>
<P>
Not only the Chinese inland areas but also Hong Kong benefited
from his policy, which brought about a vigorous economy, a
rapidly growing national gross product, and a mounting national
strength, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The glory of his achievements will shine through the ages," Li
noted.
</P>
<P>
Li went Thursday to the mourning hall at the Xinhua New Agency
Hong Kong Branch to pay homage to the deceased.
</P>
<P>
Deng's another contribution to the country and to the Chinese
nation was the "one country, two systems" concept, which led to
the successful settlement of the Hong Kong issue, said Li
Ka-shing, who is also a member of the Preparatory Committee for
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region and a Hong Kong
Affairs Advisor.
</P>
<P>
It should be attributed to Deng's wisdom and foresight that
Hong Kong maintains prosperity and stability during the transition
period and that the local people have full confidence in future,
he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
However, he voiced deep regret that Deng couldn't see with his
eyes the historic moment when Hong Kong returns to the motherland
on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Deng's passing away hasn't triggered political and economic
turbulence in China, and this testifies to Deng's vision, Li
continued.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, under the guidance of the third-generation
leadership with President Jiang Zemin at its core, China has
recorded a double-digit economic growth with inflation reined
in, an improvement in people's living standards, and an enhanced
status in the international community, he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is foreseeable that China will be an amazing economic power
in the next century, which will prove the capability of China's
third-generation leadership in governing the country," Li
stressed.
</P>
<P>
"I myself, my family and my company have full confidence in
Hong Kong's future because China is full of vigor and hope," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"The best way for me to commemorate Deng is to stay in Hong
Kong and contribute my share to the education and medical work on
the mainland," Li Ka-shing concluded.  
</P>
</TEXT>
