our region of the world," Menem said
</P>
<P>
He said that he would take the idea of the linkage to fellow
Latin American leaders upon his return.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine president said the proposed tax-free market will
benefit the 400 million potential consumers in the seven ASEAN
member countries and the 200 million people in the six nations of
the Southern Cone Common Market, or MERCOSUR.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN now groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam, while MERCOSUR
includes Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Chile, Paraguay and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
Menem arrived here Thursday after visiting Thailand and Vietnam
on what was the first visit to these countries by an Argentine
head of state. He concluded his two-day visit here and left for
home today.  
