<HEADLINE> Conference on Reporting China to Outside World (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China will resume the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong
this year, Zeng said, adding that the event, which has been
attracting worldwide attention, is an important step in the
country's reunification efforts, and will symbolize the erasure of
the nation's humiliation over the past century.
</P>
<P>
He urged those reporting on China to place more importance upon
reporting the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, as well as Deng Xiaoping's theory and practice of "one
country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return should offer a good opportunity for
reporting that will illustrate the Chinese nation's spirit to
fight against overseas aggression in the past century, and the
Chinese people's glorious history of winning independence under
the leadship of the Communist Party of China (CPC), Zeng said.
</P>
<P>
He said the coverage of the ceremony for Hong Kong's return and
other celebrations in that period should be well organized.
</P>
<P>
Economic reports will continue to dominate the work of
reporting China to the outside world, Zeng noted, adding that
reports about China's economic conditions, economic policies and
those answering overseas readers' questions should be complete,
accurate and done promptly.
</P>
<P>
When news of Deng's death was learned during the conference,
participants expressed their deep sadness, vowing to follow
closely Deng's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, and to do a better job of carrying out
international communication under the leadership of CPC Central
Committee with the President Jiang Zemin at the core. 
</P>
</TEXT>
