<HEADLINE> NPC Meeting Examines Laws and Motion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The 24th meeting of the
Standing Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress,
China's legislature, examined two draft laws and one motion today
in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Members of the committee said that the motion to establish
Chongqing in Sichuan Province as the country's forth municipality
under the direct supervision of the central government will
benefit the nation's economy.
</P>
<P>
They said that the motion, submitted by the State Council, is
in accordance with the construction of the Three Gorges Dam and
will help the relocation of the residents living in the reservoir
area.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing is the biggest industrial city on the upper reaches
of the Yangtze River. Should it become a municipality, the city's
population will balloon into 30 million, making it the largest
city in the world.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also discussed the draft law on highways, which is
expected to safeguard the interests of investors, managers and
users, according to the members.
</P>
<P>
Members also deliberated the draft law on the prevention of
livestock epidemic diseases, which will protect residents' health
and develop the rural economy.  
</P>
