<HEADLINE> China Beats Singapore 3-1 in Soccer Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 21 (Xinhua) -- China downed Singapore
3-1 in the curtain-raising game at an international soccer
tournament here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese midfielder Fan Zhiyi converted a spot kick after
forward Su Maozhen was tripped down in the penalty area 12 minutes
into action.
</P>
<P>
At the 60th minute, Chinese midfielder Li Jinyu headed home a
high pass from Sui Dongliang, putting the Chinese eleven 2-0 up.
</P>
<P>
Singapore pulled one goal back eight minutes later as Nazri
Nasir cashed in on a Chinese lapse in defence to blast home a long
shot.
</P>
<P>
Su Maozhen completed the Chinese tally nine minutes later.
</P>
<P>
In the eight-team tournament, China is bundled with Singapore,
Malaysia and Finland in Group A, and Group B includes Indonesia,
Vietnam, Zimbabwe and Bosnia-Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
China will take on Finland on Sunday. 
</P>
