<HEADLINE> China, Viet Nam to Advance Neighborly Friendly Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 21 (Xinhua) -- China and Viet Nam should view
bilateral ties from a strategic and long-term perspective, and to
boost their neighborly friendship and mutually beneficial
cooperation substantially as the 21st century draws nearer,
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark this afternoon during a meeting with
Nguyen Tan Dung, standing committee member of the Vietnamese
Communist Party (CPV) Politburo Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen first expressed his condolences to the Communist Party of
China (CPC), Chinese government and people over the death of Deng
Xiaoping, saying that Deng's name has been closely associated with
Chinese people's cause of reform and opening up.
</P>
<P>
According to Nguyen, the success of Deng's cause is of great
significance not only to China, but also to the revolutionary
movement of people all over the world.
</P>
<P>
"Deng's death is a huge loss to the CPC and the Chinese
people," he added.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his heartfelt appreciation, Jiang said the death of
Deng is an immeasurable loss to the Party, the army and the people
of all ethnic groups across China.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Communist Party, the army and the people of various
ethnic groups across the country are determined to turn grief into
strength, hold high the great banner of Deng's theory to build
socialism with Chinese characteristics, unite and continue the
great cause of socialist reforms, opening up and modernization
drive initiated by him, run China's affairs still better and make
great contributions to the cause of peace, development and
progress of the mankind, the Chinese leader said.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral ties, Jiang said China and Viet Nam, which are
socialist neighbors, have enjoyed traditional friendship between
the two peoples and the two parties.
</P>
<P>
"We're glad that our friendly cooperative relations have been
completely restored and developed over the past few years," the
president noted.
</P>
<P>
The CPC and the Chinese government highly value the relations
with Viet Nam, hoping that these relations will grow even further,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that he is very glad to see that Viet Nam has chosen
a road of development which suits its practical conditions and has
made remarkable achievements in various areas.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the Vietnamese people will make new
and greater achievements in their cause of socialist construction
and innovation under the leadership of General Secretary Do Muoi.
</P>
<P>
In reply, Nguyen said: "We are very glad to see that Chinese
people have been so successful in their reforms and opening up led
by CPC, which we take as an encouragement to us."
</P>
<P>
According to the senior Vietnamese official, the purpose of his
current visit to China is to learn more about China's experience
and successes in its reforms and opening up.
</P>
<P>
"We will work to safeguard and further promote our friendly
ties of cooperation in line with the consensus reached by the top
leaders of the two parties and countries," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
