<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Parliament Condole Deng Xiaoping's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Both houses of Indian
Parliament today condoled the death of Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping and reaffirmed India's desire to build friendly,
good-neighborly, constructive and cooperative relations with China
for the prosperity of the people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Members of Parliament observed a minute of silence as a mark of
respect to the departed soul, Press Trust of India said.
</P>
<P>
Paying homage to Deng in the Rajya Sabha (the upper house of
parliament), Chairman K.R. Narayanan, who is also vice president
of India, recalled Deng's substantial contribution in recent years
to India-China relations and said it was his historic meeting with
the then prime minister Rajiv Gandhi during his visit to China in
1988 which "reoriented our bilateral relations."
</P>
<P>
Narayanan said Rajiv Gandhi during his visit had recalled the
importance of cooperation between India and China, the need for
the two countries to develop economically and for the
establishment of a new international political order based on the
Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
In the Lok Sabha (the lower house), Speaker P.A. Sangma said
that Deng was a great leader of the Chinese people whose
contribution to the modernization of China would be ever
remembered.
</P>
<P>
Under his leadership, China launched the process of economic
reform and opening to the outside world which, Sangma said, had
been responsible for raising the standard of living of the Chinese
people and the integration of Chinese economy with that of the
world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
