<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anthrax Spreads Beyond Control Zone In Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Anthrax outbreak has spread
outside the original contained zone of Tatura-Stanhope region of
Victoria in southeast Australia, bringing the toll of cattle to
144 with five more recorded in the past 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
One of the four properties confirmed today to have the disease
was three kilometers northwest of the disease zone Tatura in the
north of Victoria state.
</P>
<P>
Since the outbreak was discovered on January 26, animals in 75
properties have contracted the disease, prompting a major
vaccination program of more than 36,000 cows.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture Minister Pat McNamara, who visited Tatura today,
said the government was considering to give help to the affected
farmers through the Rural Finance corporation.
</P>
<P>
A letter from the Victorian and federal governments has also
been sent to meat buyers, assuring them of the stringent
quarantine measures in place.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life  (18) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A scientific judgement made by Deng and the CPC about
contemporary China's basic national conditions is that China is at
the initial stage of socialism.
</P>
<P>
After the Third Plenary Session of the Eleventh Party Central
Committee, Deng pointed out that with such a poor foundation to
start, a huge population, and limited farmland, China must take a
modernization road of its own style.
</P>
<P>
In speaking about the experiences of China's socialist
construction in 1980, Deng said, "Don't use 'leftist' measures
which are divorced from reality and overstep the present-day
period of development. Such measures can not help build socialism."
</P>
<P>
On the eve of the 13th National Party Congress, Deng pointed
out, "The 13th National Party Congress must make it clear that
China's socialism is at its initial stage. Socialism itself is the
initial stage of Communism. Since China is at the initial stage of
socialism, it is at a state of underdevelopment. We must proceed
in all cases from this reality and work out our plans based on the
reality."
</P>
<P>
The 13th Congress of the CPC systematically expounded the
theory on the initial stage of socialism, and gave a brief summary
to Deng's explanations of socialism's initial stage: "Lead and
unite people of all ethnic groups of the whole country, focus on
economic construction, stick to the four cardinal principles,
stick to reforms and opening to the outside world, self-reliance
and hard work, in an effort to build China into a rich, powerful,
democratic socialist country with modernization and civilization."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life  (19) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a speech entitled "the current situation and tasks" in 1980,
Deng pointed out that there were three key tasks for the 1980s,
but the most important one was modernization. Deng urged the whole
Party to devote its efforts to this task and never let up. All
other tasks must serve the central task of economic construction.
</P>
<P>
In the development of productivity, Deng paid special attention
to the position and role of science and technology and proposed a
new idea that science and technology are the most important part
in productivity.
</P>
<P>
Believing that the key to China's modernization is the
modernization of its science and technology, He called for respect
of knowledge and talents. He emphasized that the basis of bringing
up scientific and technological talents is education. Education is
of equal importance to science and technology, and is the most
fundamental cause of a nation.
</P>
<P>
With great foresight, Deng outlined a strategy of economic
development for China. In 1979, he put forward the goal of
quadrupling the country's GNP by the end of the century and giving
most Chinese a relatively comfortable standard of living.
</P>
<P>
In his speeches over the next few years, Deng drew a three-step
blueprint for the country's development from the 1980s up to the
middle of the 21st century: The first step would double the GNP
between 1981 and 1990; the second would double the GNP a second
time and give people a relatively well-off life by the end of the
century; and the third would bring the GNP to the middle-level of
developed countries and give people a much better life and would
basically realize modernization. This development strategy was
approved at the 13th National Congress of the Chinese Communist
Party.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 14:24 </DATE_TIME>
