<HEADLINE> Kuwait Enters Huge Joint Venture in Qatar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The Kuwait National
Industries Company, a non-oil industrial complex in the country,
said today it would take part in the establishment of a 400
million U.S. dollar Qatar Hot Briquetted Iron Plant.
</P>
<P>
A contract to build the gigantic joint venture in Qatar was
signed here Thursday by the Qatari side with the Kuwaiti-based
Gulf Investment Corporation, the Kuwaiti National Industries
Company and the Canadian firm of Durerco International Investment,
Kuwait News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the three foreign firms take 16.33 percent of
the stakes in the joint venture each.
</P>
<P>
Company sources were quoted as saying the building for the
joint venture was expected to be completed in 30 months and it
would have a production capacity of 2 million tonnes of iron
annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
