<HEADLINE> Laos, Indonesia Sign MOU on Agriculture, Air Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Laos and Indonesia have reached
a memorandum of understanding (MOU) on cooperation in agriculture,
forestry and air transport, reports reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
Lao Foreign Minister Som Savat Lengsavad and his Indonesian
counterpart, Ali Alatas, who accompanied President Suharto on a
three-day visit to Laos, signed the MOU in Vientiane on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Alatas, as quoted by Lao official news agency KPL, said the
document was a hallmark for the future expansion of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The relationship between Laos and Indonesia had been formed on
a good basis, he added, noting that there was no political issue
to hinder their bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
What was left for the two countries to do now was to work
together to find ways to widen and deepen the cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Lao Prime Minister Khamtay Siphandone and Indonesian President
Suharto witnessed the signing ceremony of the MOU.
</P>
<P>
Suharto left here for Burma today, the last stop in his swing
through Cambodia, Laos and Burma. All the three countries want to
join the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), which
groups Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand,
Vietnam and Brunei. 
</P>
