<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (21) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping took opening up to the outside world as one of
the country's fundamental policies and pointed out that it is
impossible for any country to develop by adopting a policy of
isolation and seclusion. The world is indispensable to China's
development.
</P>
<P>
China must absorb all the achievements of human civilization,
he said, and it should be open to all countries in the world in a
comprehensive way, and actively develop foreign trade, expand
Sino-foreign cooperation and introduce foreign capital, advanced
technology, and managerial experiences.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, China must introduce foreign intelligence
and send a large number of students to study abroad.
</P>
<P>
Deng also made a series of important policy decisions on
establishing special economic zones, opening up a dozen of coastal
port cities, opening a coastal economic development belt, and
developing Shanghai's Pudong New Area. He made inspection tours of
the country's special economic zones in 1984 and 1992, and noted
that the special economic zones serve as the country's showcase of
technology, management, expertise, and foreign policy, with their
fast growth spurring the nationwide opening-up, which has
stimulated the country's reform and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
However, the push for reform, opening-up and socialist
modernization would not be smooth sailing Instead, it would
inevitably encounter obstacles. In the political disturbances
during the turn of Spring and Summer in 1989, Deng and other
revolutionary veterans firmly supported the resolute measures
taken by the Party and Government, which succeeded in safeguarding
national independence, dignity, security and stability.
</P>
<P>
Deng stressed in particular that reforms and economic
construction require a stable political environment, and that
stability overrides everything else. Also, he pointed out that the
Party's policies and principles drawn up since the Third Plenary
Session of the 11th Party Central Committee are all correct and
the occurrence of the event could in no way prove the set
strategic goals to be wrong. Neither adherence to the Four
Cardinal Principles nor reform and opening-up is mistaken. The
only mistake lied in inconsistent adherence to the Four Cardinal
Principles, poor work in political and ideological education, or a
situation with "one hand strong, and the other weak."
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that efforts must be made to adhere to the set
basic lines, policies and principles which will remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Deng paid great attention to socialist cultural and ideological
construction, stressing the importance of building advanced
socialist culture, ethics, and ideology, while working hard for an
advanced socialist material civilization. Only when both aspects
of the progress are achieved can it be called socialism with
Chinese characteristics, he said, pointing constantly to the need
to push for material advancement on one hand, and cultural and
ethical progress on the other, with both hands working hard all
the time. The whole people should be so educated that they have
lofty ideals, moral principles, knowledge and expertise together
with disciplines, he said, noting that efforts should be made to
make full use of China's advantages and unite the people with a
firm faith.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the National Congress of the CPC back in 1985, Deng
cautioned the Party that it would follow a crooked path and
material civilization would be hurt, if cultural and ethical
development was not sufficiently strengthened, and that revolution
and construction would not possibly succeed by depending on
material conditions alone.
</P>
<P>
Later, he added that efforts should never be loosened for a
single day to push for cultural, ethical and ideological
advancement and to build up a fine Party style and social
atmosphere. Rather, work in this regard need to be handled case by
case.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (22) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As supreme leader of the PLA, Deng put forth many important
ideas on building the army in the new phase of China's
development, providing scientific judgements on modern times and
China's security environment, and ensuring a strategic shift in
the guiding ideology for building the army and national defense.
</P>
<P>
Deng demanded that the armed forces built into a powerful,
modernized and standardized revolutionary army, working for the
modernization drive as its central task, walking along a path of
developing the best troops with Chinese characteristics, and
boosting defense capabilities to guarantee national security and
safeguard the unity of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Deng noted that the army should obey, serve, support and
participate in the country's economic construction, acting
conscientiously in this overall interest of the country.
</P>
<P>
Under his leadership, the PLA troops were cut by one million,
in a practical move of China in safeguarding world peace. In 1989,
when resigning his post as chairman of the Central Military
Commission, Deng expressed the deep conviction that the PLA will
unswerving stick to its nature, that is, an army of the Party, of
the people and of the socialist country.
</P>
<P>
To order to solve the problem of Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan
and to achieve the reunification of the motherland, Deng, by
respecting both history and realities, and by proceeding from the
actual conditions, creatively put forth the idea of "one country,
two systems", which means practising socialism on the Chinese
mainland and allowing the existence of a capitalist system in Hong
Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
In September 1982, in meeting with the British prime minister,
Deng expounded on China's basic stand on the Hong Kong issue and
defended the sovereignty and dignity of the motherland. Deng threw
his energy into the whole process of solving the problem of Hong
Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
On July 1, 1997, China will resume its exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong, thus accomplishing his great plan.
</P>
<P>
In 1983, he brought up the eight-point principle for settling
the Taiwan problem, expressing a strong wish to reunify the
motherland. In view of attempts to split China, Deng emphasized
that it won't do to give up the use of non-peaceful means to solve
the Taiwan issue. The idea of "one country, two systems"
constitutes not only an important part of the theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, but also serves as a model
for resolving similar problems elsewhere in the world.
</P>
<P>
Socialist modernization requires not only domestic stability,
but a peaceful international environment as well. Deng put forth a
full set of diplomatic strategies, sizing up the situation of the
whole world.
</P>
<P>
He defined peace and development as the two major issues of the
present world, saying China must adhere to an independent foreign
policy of peace, oppose hegemonism, and safeguard world peace. He
stood for the establishment of a new international political and
economic order with the Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence
as the norms.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China will always belong to the Third World,
and never seek hegemony. With Deng in charge, China established
diplomatic relations with the United States, signed the
Sino-Japanese peace and friendship treaty, restored relations
between the two parties and countries of China and the Soviet
Union, and developed friendly relations with neighboring countries
and many Third World nations.
</P>
<P>
He visited many countries and played host to the leaders of
many countries. Amidst a changing international situation towards
the end of the 1980s and at the beginning of the 1990s, when the
socialist cause underwent serious setbacks, Deng put forth a
strategy of studying the situation with a sober mind, holding
tight to our ground, and dealing with the challenges with calm,
stressing the need to always put national sovereignty and security
in the first place.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping contributed tremendously to ensure favorable
international conditions for China's modernization drive, and to
the cause of safeguarding world peace and the progress of all
mankind.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (23) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping always attached importance to Party building. He
held that the core of the Four Cardinal Principles is to stick to
the Party leadership, which is the key to realization of the
four-modernization program.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that to adhere to and strengthen the Party
leadership, efforts should be made to improve the Party
leadership, status of its work and organization, and system of
leadership.
</P>
<P>
Deng said that efforts should be focused on the Party building,
in order to build the Party into a staunch core to lead the people
throughout the country in promoting material civilization and
socialist cultural and ethical progress.
</P>
<P>
Great heed should be paid to studying Marxist theory, and the
sense of principle, systematization, foresight, and creativeness
should be enhanced.
</P>
<P>
He said that the democratic centralism should be adhered to and
further improved and the central authority should be maintained.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that the key to rectifying social atmosphere
hinges on improvement of Party style. It's essential to carry
forward the style of hard work and forging close ties with the
masses. In the entire process of reforms and opening up to the
outside world, corruption should be resolutely opposed. And
building a clean and honest government should be taken as a major
task.
</P>
<P>
In view of the future of the Party and the nation, Deng firmly
stood for eradicating the life tenure of leading officials and he
personally took the lead in doing so.
</P>
<P>
He himself had asked time and again for retirement from leading
posts. He no longer participated in the CPC Central Committee and
Central Advisory Commission at the 13th National Congress of the
CPC in November 1987.
</P>
<P>
At the Fifth Plenum of the 13th CPC Central Committee in
November, 1989, Deng again resigned from his post as chairman of the
Central Military Commission, realizing his long-cherished wish of
resigning from all his posts.
</P>
<P>
He played a crucial role in promoting a smooth transition from
the second generation of leadership with himself at the core to the
third generation with Jiang Zemin at the core and safeguarding the
stability of the Party and the country.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the core of the first generation of Party
leadership was Chairman Mao, and that he could be taken as the
head of the second generation, he said the third generation must
also have a core; that is Comrade Jiang Zemin, and everybody
should safeguard this collective leadership and its core. "This
is my political accountability," he said.
</P>
<P>
Although he quit his leading posts, Deng followed with concern
the reforms, opening-up, and modernization drive with a tremendous
sense of historical responsibility.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (24) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In early 1992, Deng made an inspection tour of Wuchang,
Shenzhen, Zhuhai, Shanghai and other southern places, and made
important remarks, summerizing the Party's basic practices and
experience since the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC Central
Committee held in late 1978, and answered a number of major
questions that had puzzled and confined people's thinking
frequently.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the nature of socialism is the liberation of
productive forces, developing productivity, eradicating
exploitation and eliminating polarization, and eventually
achieving common prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The criterion to tell the right from the wong in various fields
of work, he said, should be taken into account whether it is
favorable for the development of productive forces in socialist
society, whether it is favorable for strengthening the
comprehensive national strength, and whether it is favorable for
the improvement of people's standard of living."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that bolder efforts should be made in reform and
opening up to the outside world and opportune time should be
seized to develop China itself and the crux is economic
development.
</P>
<P>
He said the Party's basic political line should be kept to
unswervingly for 100 years.
</P>
<P>
His talks provide ample theoretical preparations for the
convening of the Party's 14th National Congress, held in October,
1992, which advocated that Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics must be used to arm the
whole party and designated the establishment of the socialist
market economy as the goal of reform.
</P>
<P>
China's reforms, opening-up, and modernization drive entered a
new phase, epitomized by Deng's talks in the south and the Party's
14th National Congress.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, 89-year-old Deng was personally in charge of compiling
the third volume of the Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping and
finalized each of is articles. The second and third volumes
collected his major creative works in the cause of shaping and
developing his theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics. They are scientific guidelines for China's
socialist reforms, opening-up and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
The theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics
created by Deng Xiaoping is the product of combining the basic
principles of Maxism and Leninism with the reality of contemporary
China and the features of the times, representing the inheritance
and development of Mao Zedong thought and Marxism of contemporary
China. It has become the most precious ideological assets of the
Chinese Communist Party and the entire Chinese people, and serves
as the spiritual prop in the invigoration and development of the
Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Guided by this theory, the Chinese people are successfully
marching towards the 21st century under the leadership of the CPC
Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines to Improve Trade Ties With S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Bilateral trade relations
between the Philippines and South Africa are expected to improve
further with the forthcoming visit of South African President
Nelson Mandela slated for March 1-3, the Philippine News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said Mandela's state visit, the first ever by a
South African head of state, will focus primarily on the
improvement and promotion of trade and investments between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the two countries will sign a trade
agreement, a memorandum of understanding on tourism development
and an air services agreement, it said.
</P>
<P>
South Africa remains the Philippines' top trading partner among
African countries and the country's 30th top export market in the
world.
</P>
<P>
Data from the Philippine National Statistics Office show that
the country's exports to South Africa jumped 31.8 percent last
year to 30.28 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
