<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Vice President, Party Leaders Condole Deng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 21 (Xinhua) -- India's Vice President K.R.
Narayanan today went to the Chinese Embassy in India to condole
the passing away of Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
He said, "In the passing away of Deng Xiaoping the world has
lost one of the leaders who has made history in the 20th century.
But his ideas and contribution will influence and enrich the 21st
century."
</P>
<P>
"As an Indian I am grieved by his passing away. He has opened a
new and friendly phase in the relations between India and China,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from India's major political parties such as the
Congress party, the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP), the Communist
Party of India and the Communist Party of India (Marxism), today
also went to the Chinese Embassy to express their deep grief and
sorrow over the passing away of Deng Xiaoping.  
</P>
</TEXT>
