<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen to Raise Overseas Fund for Building of Expressways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to an executive of Shenzhen Expressways Co. Ltd, the
money will be used mainly to construct the western section of the
expressway linking He'ao to the airport in Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
The 44.3-km-long expressway is expected to be completed in June
of 1999, said the executive.
</P>
<P>
Set up by three local companies, Shenzhen Expressways
Co. Ltd. oversees four highways that collect fees, including
Meilin-Guanlan and He'ao-Airport expressways, and enjoys certain
privileges given by the Shenzhen City Government for development
and management.
</P>
<P>
Shares of the company will be underwritten by a joint
international underwriting group, according to the source, and
sales promotional events for the shares will be held in Hong Kong
on February 24, and later in a dozen cities in other countries,
including Britain, Japan, the United States and
Switzerland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
