<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Stronger at Weekend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar today
ended more than half a U.S. cent higher.
</P>
<P>
It settled at 77.45 U.S. cents, up from 76.88 at the close of
previous session.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rates, the Australian dollar ended at 94.19
Japanese yen, down from 95.15 Wednesday, and at 1.3053 Deutsche
marks from 1.3001.  
</P>
