<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Slightly Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The Australian shares market
recovered some of their earlier losses today as shining gold and
resource stocks led the market upward in afternoon trading.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index bounced back from a low of 2460.6
points recorded this morning to close only one point weaker at
2475.3 from Wednesday's close.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index closed 11.1 points softer at 3858.0,
while the all resources gained 7.9 points to 1413.8.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 415.48 million shares, valued at
934.51 million Australian dollars (724.24 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
