<HEADLINE> Prokurorov Wins Title in Freestyle Cross Country Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Alexi Prokurorov
won the 30-kilometer freestyle cross country world championship
event in Trondheim, Norway on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Prokurorov completed the race with a time of one hour 6 minutes
28.2 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Norway's Bjorn Daehlie finished second in one hour 6 minutes
45.2 seconds and his compatriot Thomas Aalsgaard came third in one
hour 6 minutes 49.2 seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
