<HEADLINE> S'pore Leaders Pay Respects to Late Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's leaders today
paid their last respects to the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping,
a man they described as a giant among world leaders.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong arrived at the Chinese Embassy
here in the afternoon for a short solemn visit. He wrote on the
condolence book, "My condolence with profound respect."
</P>
<P>
Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew, who called Deng Xiaoping the man
who saved China, also came to pay his tribute to Deng's
achievements.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Goh Keng Swee, former deputy prime minister, who has been
China's special economic advisor, also gave high praise for the
late Chinese leader.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister S. Jayakumar came to the Chinese Embassy late
this afternoon and expressed his condolences to Chinese Ambassador
Fu Xuezhang.
</P>
<P>
Other Members of Parliament (MPs) and former MPs also paid
their last respects to Deng at the Chinese Embassy.  
</P>
