<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life  (15) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Third Plenary Session of the Eleventh Central Committee of
the CPC in December of 1978 marked a great turning-point in the
history of the Party and the country and ushered in a new era of
development of the socialist cause.
</P>
<P>
In his speech entitled "Emancipate mind, seek truth from facts,
and unite as one to look forward" at a working conference of the
Party Central Committee held before the plenary session, Deng
noted that, "Emancipation of the mind is an important political
issue at the moment.
</P>
<P>
"If a party, a country or a nation proceeds in all cases like a
bookworshiper, with ossified thought, and practises superstition
enthusiastically, it will not make any progress, its life will
come to an end and the Party and the country will perish.
</P>
<P>
"Democracy is an important condition for the emancipation of
mind," he said, and "We must institutionalize and legalize
democracy.", "We must study new situations and solve new
problems." He emphasized, "If we do not start the reforms right
now, our cause of modernization and the cause of socialism will be
ruined."
</P>
<P>
Deng also initiated the policy of allowing certain areas and
certain people to become wealthier first, so that they in turn
would help other areas and other people to get rich. As a result,
the whole national economy would develop and bring the people of
all ethnic groups to a better life at a relatively fast pace.
</P>
<P>
This policy was of great importance, and the speech served as
the key-note speech for the plenary session.
</P>
<P>
The session reestablished the thinking mode of emancipating
mind and seeking truth from facts, and firmly put an end to the
use of the erroneous slogan "Take class struggle as the key link."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0130 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (16) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Third Plenary Session shifted the Party and State's work
priority to the construction of socialist modernization and put
forward the strategic policy of reform and opening to the outside
world.
</P>
<P>
The second collective leadership with Deng Xiaoping at the core
came into being after this plenary session.
</P>
<P>
Deng paid close attention to dealing with the matter of the
Party's organizational line. In many of his speeches, Deng
emphasized that the materialization of ideological and political
lines should be guaranteed by the organizational line. He adopted
a series of measures to make cadres more revolutionary, younger,
more knowledgeable and more professional. And he abolished the
system of lifetime tenure of leading cadres and set up a new
system of cooperation and succession for older and younger cadres.
</P>
<P>
A rightist trend of getting rid of the Party leadership and
opposing the socialist road began to emerge in the process of
setting things to right and correcting the "leftist" mistakes.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to maintain correct orientation in the
modernization drive, Deng gave a speech entitled "Sticking to the
Four Cardinal Principles" in March of 1979 at a theory meeting
convened by the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Taking a clear-cut stand, Deng proposed that China stick to the
socialist road, stick to the people's democratic dictatorship,
stick to the leadership of the Chinese Communist Party, and stick
to Marxism, Leninism and Mao Zedong Thought. "These are the
prerequisites of realizing the four modernizations," he said, "If
any one of the four cardinal principles is shaken, it means the
shaking of the whole socialist cause and the whole cause of
modernization."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0131 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (17) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Sixth Plenary Session of the Eleventh CCP Central Committee
in June of 1981 passed a resolution on a number of historical
issues after the founding of the People's Republic of China in
1949.
</P>
<P>
The resolution summarized past experience, refuted the
"Cultural Revolution", and gave a scientific assessment on Mao
Zedong Thought to secure Mao's historical status.
</P>
<P>
The subsequent domestic developments and changes in the
international situation served to demonstrate Deng's great courage
and vision in making this important decision. At the plenary
session, Deng was elected chairman of the Central Military
Commission.
</P>
<P>
The 12th National Congress of the CCP was held in September of
1982. At the opening session, Deng called on the Party to "combine
the universal truth of Marxism with the specific conditions of our
country, take our own road and build socialism with Chinese
characteristics." The Congress adopted a programme of creating a
new situation in the socialist modernization.
</P>
<P>
Deng was elected a member of the Standing Committee of the CPC
Central Committee's Political Bureau and appointed chairman of the
Central Military Commission, at the First Session of the Twelfth
Central Committee. A Central Advisory Commission was set up at the
Congress and Deng was elected chairman of the commission at its
first plenary session.
</P>
<P>
In the years following the Third Plenary Session of the
Eleventh Central Committee, Deng focused on the meaning of
socialism and how to build socialism, and for the first time gave
a systematic, tentative answer to such basic questions as to how
to build, consolidate and develop socialism in such an
economically and culturally backward country like China. Deng
developed Marxism, Leninism and Mao Zedong Thought with new
thoughts and new ideas.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0132 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France to Fence in World Cup Crowds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 21 (Xinhua) -- France will keep fences to
separate the fans from the pitches in the 10 soccer stadiums to be
used for the 1998 World Cup soccer finals.
</P>
<P>
Interior minister Jean-Louis Debre told the sports daily
l'Equipe on Friday he could not take the risk of pulling fences
down.
</P>
<P>
"I can only say that to assure the security in a competition of
this size there can be no question about taking fences down," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"With Guy Drut, the sports minister, we carried out a survey
and came to the conclusion it would not be possible to take fences
down. We aren't ready for it," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKSAR Provisional Legislature To Meet in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional Legislative
Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) will hold a meeting tomorrow in Shenzhen, the Chinese city
bordering Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the tentative legislature is to formally
set up two working groups to determine working rules and to study
the administrative framework of the PLC, said Rita Fan, the PLC
president. Lists of the 12 members for each ad hoc team, one on
administrative matters and the other on rules of procedures, will
be announced tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
The two working groups will then meet concurrently to elect
their convenors and formulate future work plans. Finally, the
convenors of each team will move respective resolutions to the PLC
for endorsement.
</P>
<P>
According to Rita Fan, before June 30, 1997, the PLC will hold
its plenary meeting in Shenzhen in order to respect the British
governing of Hong Kong. During the period, the interim body will
make preparations for the legislative work after July 1, 1997, so
that it will by no means affect the operation of the current
Legislative Council under the Hong Kong British government, said
the PLC president.
</P>
<P>
Founded on December 21, 1996, the PLC will continue to operate
until the first Legislative Council of the HKSAR is elected around
June 30, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
