<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canadians Win World Cup Aerial Event Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Canadians swept the top spots
in both the men's and women's aerial event at the World Cup
freestyle skiing meet in Kirchberg, Austria on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Jeff Bean won the men's title with 230.91 points, ahead of
fellow Canadians Nicolas Fontaine with 230.73 and Andy Capicik
with 226.46. Fontaine leads the World Cup standings with 556
points.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Jean-Damien Climonet was fourth with 209.97 points,
and Britt Swartley of the United States came fifth with 204.24
points.
</P>
<P>
In the women's event, Carolie Olivier of Canada took first
place with 172.27 points and her compatriot Veronica Brenner was
second with 172.13 points respecively. Natalya Orechova of Russia
finished third with 171.62 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
