<HEADLINE> Research on the National Defense Industry Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Research into the science,
technology and industrial development of China's national defense
sector should be enhanced, Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a national working meeting for the sector, the vice
premier stressed that the quality of industrial products for
defense should be further guaranteed, and the production aim of
more enterprises should be changed from making products solely for
military use to goods for civilian use.
</P>
<P>
"Quality is the lifeline and of vital importance to the defense
industrial sector," he said.
</P>
<P>
He encouraged the related departments to follow more closely
the advanced defense technologies in the world so as to improve
China's weapons.
</P>
<P>
"Every military enterprise should develop its own products of
civil use in order to make direct contributions to the nation's
economic development," the vice premier stressed. Endiem

