<HEADLINE> Zambian President Condoles Deng at Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba today went to the Chinese Embassy in Lusaka and condoled
late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping who had passed away in Beijing
on Wednesday night at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian president extolled Deng as a great historical
figure and a great friend to the people of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said the blueprint Deng designed for China nearly 20
years ago has benefited not only the Chinese people but the whole
world.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that the Chinese people will continue
the program of reform outlined by Deng.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Vice-President Godfrey Miyanda, cabinet ministers,
foreign envoys to Zambia, members of Chinese institutions and
companies, and other Chinese residents in Zambia, also went to
the Chinese Embassy to pay their tributes to Deng. 
