<HEADLINE> Mozambican President Condoles Deng at Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano today went to Chinese Embassy in Maputo and mourned late
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping who had passed away on Wednesday
night at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
"I hereby express my deep sorrow over the passing away of Deng
Xiaoping who is not only an outstanding leader of the Chinese
Communist Party and the People's Republic of China, but also a
great friend of Mozambique," Chissano wrote in the embassy's
visitors' book.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambican president, accompanied by Prime Minister
Pascoal Mocumbi, Foreign Minister Leonardo Simao and other
top-ranking government officials, paid one minute's silent
tribute to Deng's portrait during the mourning.
</P>
<P>
"As China mourned the great leader nationwide, I, on behalf of
the people and government of Mozambique as well as myself, would
like to express profound condolences to Deng's family," Chissano
wrote.
</P>
<P>
He praised Deng as one of the recognized international
political leaders of the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
Other Mourners at the Chinese Embassy included delegates of
the ruling Mozambique Liberation Front (PRELIMO), representatives
of the local mass organizations, foreign envoys in Maputo and
overseas Chinese living or working in Mozambique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
