<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 12:32 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait's Revenues Increase by Nearly One-Fifth, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti actual revenues
for the fiscal year of 1995-96 ending June 30 stood at 11.5
billion U.S. dollars, an increase of 19.3 percent over the budget
estimate.
</P>
<P>
The Al-Shall weekly report today quoted a Kuwaiti Audit Bureau
report on revenues and expenditures in the fiscal year 1995-1996
as saying that actual revenues reached 3.472 billion Kuwaiti
dinars (around 11.5 billion U.S. dollars), 563 million dinars (1.86
billion U.S. dollars) higher than the estimates.
</P>
<P>
The report said that oil revenues reached 3.114 billion dinars
(over 9.3 billion dollars), constituting 89.7 percent of total
revenues, while primary estimates had put oil revenues at 2.49
billion dinars (about 7.4 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The increase in oil revenues was achieved due to a price hike
in the international crude markets last year. Kuwait exports
about 2 million barrels of crude oil per day.
</P>
<P>
But the report said some of the oil revenue increase was
countered with a 360-million-dinar (over 1.08 billion dollars)
decrease in non-oil revenues.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kuwaiti actual expenditures decreased by 2.5
percent, standing at 4.127 billion dinars (over 12.38 billion
dollars) compared with the budgeted 4.23 billion dinars (over
12.69 billion dollars), the report said.
</P>
<P>
Actual revenue rise has resulted in a substantial decrease of
expected budget deficit in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the previous data, the report said, Kuwaiti
budget deficit in the fiscal year 1995-96 dropped by about 50
percent from an estimate of 1.377 billion dinars (4.55 billion
dollars) to 654 million dinars (2.2 billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Brilliant Life (12) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deng was in charge of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee for as long as a decade, during which China began the
building of socialism in an all-round way, and the entire Chinese
people, under the leadership of the Communist Party of China, made
great achievements in socialist economic and cultural
construction, and accumulated important experience, while some
serious mistakes were made.
</P>
<P>
For a long time Deng served in the front lines of central
leadership, taking part in making major Party and State decisions
and offering important and correct opinions in many areas. These
were the busiest years of his life. He was active in implementing
the line of the 8th CPC National Congress, pointing out that the
major task was construction and that the Cummunist Party should
accept supervision.
</P>
<P>
In 1958, when the "Great Leap Forward" began and "People's
Communes" were organized throughout the country, "Leftist" errors
began flooding in, followed by three years of difficulties in the
national economy. To summarize experiences and lessons and to
restore normal operations of the national economy, Deng made
investigations in rural areas and put forward many corrective
opinions on some major problems. He was in charge of drafting the
regulations for State enterprises, playing an important role in
the recovery of normal production order, improving and
strengthening enterprise management. He also guided the drafting
of rules for higher eduction institutions under the Ministry of
Education.
</P>
<P>
In February, 1962, the CPC Central Committee held a working
conference attended by 7,000 people to summarize experience, seek
unity of thinking, strengthen unity, and further correct the
errors caused since the Great Leap Forward. In a speech at the
meeting, Deng stressed the importance of upholding democratic
centralism, improving the democratic life of the Party, and
carrying on its fine traditions.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0148 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (13) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In May the same year, he proposed to rehabilitate the wronged
cadred once and for all. In 1962, many officials and people in
rural areas demanded a household responsibility system, because of
serious damages to the rural collective economy by the Great Leap
Forward and People's Communes. So, in July, 1962, Deng suggested
that any productive measure that is good for recovery and for
developing agriculture should be used, and that any method the
people like should be used.
</P>
<P>
While he was general-secretary of the CPC Central Committee,
Deng kept wide contacts with communist party leaders of other
countries. He headed delegations to Moscow for talks with the
Soviet Communist Party many times, during which he upheld the CPC
principle of maintaining independence and initiative.
</P>
<P>
In 1966, Mao Zedong launched the cultural revolution, and
during the next 10 years, Deng was criticized and attacked twice
and removed from all posts. This was the most difficult and
tortuous period in his life. In October, 1969, he was sent to
Xinjian county in east China's Jiangxi Province where he worked at
a bench for half a day every day in a tractor repair factory.
</P>
<P>
During this time, he read a lot of Marxist and Leninist works
and numerous classical and modern Chinese and foreign books. After
Lin Biao's counterrevolutionary plot was smashed, Mao Zedong
developed the idea of letting Deng come back to work. With Zhou
Enlai's support, Deng was reinstated as vice-premier of the State
Council in 1973. He spoke on behalf of the Chinese government at
the United Nations' 6th Special Conference in 1974, systematically
explaining Mao Zedong's theory of the three worlds.
</P>
<P>
In preparing the 4th National People's Congress and considering
the list of candidates for the leadership of the State Council,
Mao said that Deng is "a kind of capable person who is hard to
find and is strong politically and ideologically". Deng was put in
charge of drafting the government work report delivered by Zhou
Enlai at the 1st Plenary Session of the 4th National People's
Congress.
</P>
<P>
In January, 1975, Deng was appointed vice-chairman of the CPC
Central Committee, vice-premier of the State Council,
vice-chairman of the CPC Central Military Commission, and chief of
the PLA General Staff.
</P>
<P>
When Zhou Enlai became seriously ill, Deng handled routine
matters for the CPC, the government, and the military under the
support of Mao Zedong. He fought against the "Gang of Four" tit
for tat and made big efforts to rectify the chaotic situation
brought by the cultural revolution, urging the whole nation to
maintain stability and unite as one to improve the national
economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0149 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (14) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taking the railways as a starting point for rectifying the
economy, he instructed departments concerned to draft three
documents: "Some Problems on Speeding Industrial Development",
"Some Problems With Regard to Science and Technology Work" (an
outline of work report) and "On the General Program for All Fields
of Work for the Whole Party and Nation". In a short period of
time, rectifications in the army, industry, agriculture,
communications, science, education, literature and art scored
notable achievements. It was for this that he was supported by the
whole nation.
</P>
<P>
In the beginning, Mao gave him support, but ultimately could
not put up with Deng's systematic correction of the errors of the
cultural revolution and once again launched a campaign to
"criticize Deng and fight back the trend of rightists reversing
verdicts."
</P>
<P>
Zhou Enlai died in January, 1976, and on April 5, there was a
mass demonstration in Tian'anmen Square to mourn Premier Zhou, to
combat the Gang of Four, and to support Deng Xiaoping. The Gang of
Four seized the opportunity to make a case against Deng, and again
he was wrongly dismissed from all posts in the Party and
government.
</P>
<P>
Then, in September, Mao passed away, and in October the Gang of
Four was destroyed and the cultural revolution ended.
</P>
<P>
Which road China should take in the future was a major issue at
the time about which hundreds of millions of Chinese were deeply
concerned. Deng Xiaoping enjoyed very high prestige in the Party
and among the people because he had performed immense feats in the
Chinese revolution and had had great achievements in fighting
against the Gang of Four and in the overall correcting of the
chaotic situation.
</P>
<P>
With the support of Ye Jianying, Chen Yun and others, the 3rd
Plenary Session of the 10th CPC Central Committee decided to
reinstate Deng Xiaoping as vice-chairman of the CPC Central
Committee, vice-premier of the State Council, vice-chairman of the
Central Military Commission, and chief of the PLA General Staff in
July, 1977.
</P>
<P>
At the 11th National Congress of the CPC in August, 1977, Deng
was elected vice-chairman of the CPC Central Committee. In March,
1978, he was elected chairman of the 5th National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
In facing up to the many problems that still had to be dealt
with in the country, Deng showed his foresight and wisdom as a
strategist as soon as he came out to work. Grasping the decisive
link among numerous issues, he first promoted rectification on the
ideological front, and led and supported discussions on the
criteria for judging truth.
</P>
<P>
In his "Speech at the Political Work Conference of the Whole
Aarmy" and his talk "Upholding the Banner of Mao Zedong Thought
and Adhering to the Principle of Seeking Truth From Facts", he
opposed the erroneous idea of "two whatevers" that says, "We
should firmly uphold whatever policy decisions Chairman Mao made,
and we should unswervingly adhere to whatever instructions
Chairman Mao gave." Deng pointed out that it is necessary to
understand Mao Zedong Thought in an overall and accurate way,
saying that "seeking truth from facts is the basic point of
departure of Mao Zedong Thought". The deadlock that froze people's
minds for long was broken.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
