<HEADLINE> Malaysian Leaders Pay Tribute to Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad and Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi today
paid tribute to the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir regarded Deng as the main architect of China's drive
for reforms towards modernization and the adoption of an open
policy.
</P>
<P>
Deng was also responsible for enhancing China's role in the
maintenance of world peace and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
Deng's death was "not only a great loss to China but also to
the world," Mahathir said in his condolence message to Chinese
Premier Li Peng which was released by the Foreign Ministry here
today.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said Deng's innovative approach to China's development
through his doctrine of socialism with Chinese characteristics,
bold vision and outstanding leadership was fundamental in charting
the course of China's dynamic economic development.
</P>
<P>
"China's burgeoning economy today is testimony of the
resounding success of his pragmatic policies," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Deng's "many visits abroad resulted in China's close
relations, particularly with her neighbors in the East Asian
region."
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian leader said the people of Malaysia recalled
fondly his memorable visit to Malaysia in November 1978 which
paved the way for closer bilateral relations and cooperation
between Malaysia and China.
</P>
<P>
"As the nation mourns his passing, may I extend, on behalf of
the government and people of Malaysia, our deepest sympathy and
heartfelt condolences to Your Excellency and, through you, to
members of the bereaved family," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian Foreign Minister today also praised Deng for his
tremendous contributions to China and for being instrumental in
paving the way towards Beijing's economic modernization reforms in
his letter of condolence to Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah said as an outstanding statesman, Deng had made an
important contribution towards regional and international peace
and stability.
</P>
<P>
"His demise would be strongly felt not just by the Chinese
people but also by the world community," Abdullah said.  
</P>
