<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Deng Xiaoping was an
outstanding leader whose high prestige was recognized by the
Party, the military, and the people of all ethnic groups
throughout China. He was a great Marxist, a great proletarian
revolutionary, statesman, military strategist and diplomat, and a
long tested communist fighter, the chief architect of China's
socialist reforms, opening up, and modernization drive, and the
founder of the theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping's life was a brilliant life as a fighter. In his
magnificent revolutionary career spanning more than seven decades,
he made indelible contributions to the victory of China's New
Democratic Revolution and the founding of New China, and to the
establishment, consolidation and growth of socialism in China.
</P>
<P>
He was born August 22, 1904, in Paifang village, Xiexing
township of Guangan County, in Sichuan Province. His original name
was Deng Xiansheng. Where he was sent to an old-style school at
the age of five, he was given the school name of Deng
Xixian. Afterwards he transferred to a new-style primary school,
then went on to Guangan County High School, after passing the
entrance exam. In the fall of 1919, he went to Chongqing
Preparatory School for students going to France on a work-study
program.
</P>
<P>
There he was influenced by the May 4 Movement, and began to
embrace the idea of "Saving China by Developing Industry". He and
his schoolmates took part in the campaign to boycott Japanese
goods and to condemn China's traitors. In the summer of 1920 he
went to France on the work-study program.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
