<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Textiles Consultations with U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong and the United
States will hold consultations on February 24 in Washington D.C.
on a range of ongoing textile issues.
</P>
<P>
An official release said here today that Deputy
Director-General of Trade Rebecca Lai will lead a Hong Kong
delegation to talk with the U.S. side which will be led by Deputy
Chief Textile Negotiator Caroyl Miller.
</P>
<P>
The release said the consultations will mainly cover three
ongoing issues including matters arising from different textile
import and export datum adopted by the two sides respectively; the
change in the U.S. origin rules for textiles and clothing products
and notification of administrative arrangements for submission to
the World Trade Organization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
