<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0168 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In December of 1939, when the War of Resistance Against Japan
was stalemated, Kuomintang diehards started the First Upsurge
against Communist Party-led forces with large-scale military
attacks on the Taihang District, where the headquarters of the
Eighth Route Army and the 129th Division were located.
</P>
<P>
In March, 1940, at the head of troops from the
Shanxi-Qahar-Hebei Military Region, Deng and Liu struck back and
completely destroyed the Kuomintang diehards' force of more than
10,000 men.
</P>
<P>
To halt the Japanese army's mopping-up operations against the
base areas of north China, and to stop the Japanese "prisoner's
cage" policy beginning August of 1940, the Eighth Route Army began
large-scale sabotage of Japanese-held communication lines and
strongholds in north China, known as the "Great Campaign of One
Hundred Regiments".
</P>
<P>
In this campaign, the 38 regiments under Liu and Deng's command
fought more than 500 small and large battles, dealing a heavy blow
to the Japanese army and their puppet troops.
</P>
<P>
In September of 1942, Deng assumed the post of secretary of the
Taihang Sub-Bureau of the CPC Central Committee. In October of the
next year, when Peng Dehuai and Liu Bocheng went back to Yan'an to
take part in the Rectification Movement, he became acting
secretary of the Northern Bureau of the CPC Central Committee,
taking charge of the work of the Eighth Route Army headquarters
and all-round work to lead the Party, the government, and the
military in anti-Japanese base areas in the enemy's rear areas in
north China.
</P>
<P>
Adhering to the principles of facing the enemy-occupied area,
facing the communication lines, and advancing while the enemy
troops advances, he engaged in active and flexible guerrilla
warfare, and directed the troops to smash the mopping-up
operations of the Japanese army and their puppet troops.
</P>
<P>
He also scored great successes in leading the area in building
the Party, the army, and political power, and in carrying out a
series of movements, such as the Rectification Movement, effecting
Better Troops and Streamlined Administration, Reducing Land Rent
and Loan Interest, and launching the Great Production Campaign.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In October of 1934, Deng joined the Long March of the Central
Red Army, and became secretary general of the CPC Central
Committee at the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
In January, 1935, he participated in the Zunyi Meeting, which
established the correct leadership of a new CPC Central Committee,
represented by Mao Zedong, marking a great, significant turn in
the history of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
After the First and the Fourth Front Red Armies joined forces,
he served as head of propaganda of the Political Department of the
First Army Group, and later became deputy director and director of
the Department.
</P>
<P>
In 1937, the Japanese imperialists launched an all-round war of
aggression against China. Facing a powerful enemy, the Kuomintang
and the CPC began their second cooperation. The Chinese Workers'
and Peasants' Red Army was re-designated as the Eighth Route Army
of the National Revolutionary Army.
</P>
<P>
In August 1937, Deng was appointed deputy director of the
Political Department of the Eighth Route Army and hurried to the
front in the War of Resistance against Japan in north China. In
January of 1938, he became the political commissar of the 129th
Division of the Eighth Route Army, with Liu Bocheng as
commander-in-chief.
</P>
<P>
Deng and Liu led the 129th Division far into rear areas of
Japanese occupied territory, and tried to expand into the plains
with the help of mountainous areas, with the Taihang Mountains as
the center.
</P>
<P>
When getting a firm foothold in the Taihang Mountains after a
series of battles, they sent troops to arouse the masses of
people, organize anti-Japanese armed forces, and set up
anti-Japanese democratic power, founding the Shanxi-Hebei-Henan
Anti-Japanese Base Area.
</P>
<P>
They then led their troops to cross the Beiping-Hankou Railway,
marched eastward to the plains of southern Hebei Province, and set
up the South Hebei Anti-Japanese Base. They also founded the
Taiyue Base and the Hebei-Shandong-Henan Base, formed from a
number of smaller base areas, such as West Shandong Base.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After the victory in the War of Resistance against Japanese
Aggression, the Kuomintang, while negotiating a peace settlement
with the CPC, launched a series of local wars.
</P>
<P>
The Shanxi-Hebei-Shandong-Henan Liberated Area in the Central
China Plain, under the leadership of Liu Bocheng and Deng
Xiaoping, blocked the passage of Kuomintang troops to the North
and Northeast China Liberated areas and was a key strategic
military area.
</P>
<P>
This area bore the brunt of the Kuomintang force. In September
1945, Deng and Liu were in command at the famous Shangdang
Campaign. During the campaign all the Kuomintang troops invading
the interior of the liberated area were wiped out, and the
Shanxi-Hebei-Shandong-Henan Liberated Area was consolidated.
</P>
<P>
Later, Deng and Liu led a march eastward to intercept
Kuomintang troops heading northward along the Beiping-Hankou
Railway Line, and achieved a victory at Handan Campaign.
</P>
<P>
The two victories effectively halted Kuomintang troops' attacks
on liberated areas and greatly strengthened CPC status in
negotiations in Chongqing, playing a significant role in reaching
an armistice agreement.
</P>
<P>
In June 1946, Chiang Kai-shek launched an all-out civil
war. Liu Bocheng and Deng Xiaoping led the main force of the
Shanxi-Hebei-Shandong-Henan Field Army in mobile warfare north and
south of the Longhai (Lianyungong-Lanzhou) Railway, advancing and
retreating with big strokes and fighting continuously large-scale
battles at Longhai, Dingtao and Juye, wiping out effective
strength of Kuomintang troops in big numbers.
</P>
<P>
In May 1947, Deng served as secretary o the Central China
Plains Bureau of the CPC Central Committee. In June of that year,
in accordance with strategic arrangements made by the CPC Central
Committee and Mao Zedong on changing strategic defense to
strategic attack and taking the war to Kuomintang-ruled areas, he
and Liu led the 120,000-strong main force of the
Shanxi-Hebei-Shandong-Henan Field Army in crossing the natural
barrier of the Yellow River and eliminating more than 56,000 enemy
troops in southwest Shandong Province after 28 days of continuous
fighting, thereby opening the passageway southward.
</P>
<P>
His troops later fell on the enemy suddenly, driving straight
in, fighting in front and in the rear while being pursued by tens
of thousands of enemy troops, and marching hundreds of kilometers
to the Dabie Mountains, a prelude to the strategic offensive in
the Chinese People's War of Liberation.
</P>
<P>
After entering the Dabie Mountain area, the troops of Liu and
Deng constituted a direct threat to the vast Kuomintang-ruled
areas south of the Yangtze River, forcing the Kuomintang troops to
send their main force back to assist.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng Xiaoping's Great, Brilliant Life (9) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a result, the number of enemy troops encircling the Dabie
Mountain area was increased to about 200,000, making the struggle
there extremely difficult. Deng encouraged troops by saying: "As
long as we shoulder the heavy burden in the Dabie Mountains, other
troops and areas will be able to wipe out large numbers of enemy
troops and carry on the work in a thoroughgoing way. This is
extremely helpful for the overall situation. We must hold on no
matter how weak we become and what kind of hardships we have to
endure."
</P>
<P>
Liu and Deng led the troops and people in the Dabie Mountain
Revolutionary Base to attack enemy troops in an active and
flexible way, breaking rounds of the "encirclement and
suppression" by large numbers of Kuomintang troops in the
mountainous area.
</P>
<P>
Liu's and Deng's troops in the Dabie Mountains formed a
triangle in the central Chinese area with two other field armies
marching southward, thereby containing 90 of the over 160 enemy
brigades stationed on the southern line, extending the battle
front from south and north of the Yellow River to the northern
bank of the Yangtze River, and changing Central China from an
important rear area where Kuomintang troops attacked liberated
areas into a forward position for the PLA to win the national
victory.
</P>
<P>
In May 1948, Deng Xiaoping served as the first secretary of the
enlarged Central China Plains Bureau of the CPC Central Committee,
and as political commissar of the Central China Plains Military
Command and the Central China Plains Field Army.
</P>
<P>
In the course of establishing the New Central China Plains
Liberated Area, Deng, in his speeches and instructions, expressed
the following topics: "Victorious Situation after We Marched into
the Central China Plains and Our Future Policy and Tactics";
"Implementing the Instructions of the CPC Central Committee on
Land Reform and the Work to Consolidate the Party"; and "Views on
Entering New Areas in the Future".
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the principle of the CPC Central Committee
and proceeding from specific conditions in the newly liberated
parts of central China, Deng raised many important views and
suggestions on Party consolidation, land reform, and industrial
and commercial policies. His views and suggestions got approval
and praise from the CPC Central Committee and Mao Zedong.
</P>
<P>
Since the spring of 1948, the Central China Plains Field Army
cooperated with the East China Field Army to fight a series of
battles at Luoyang, Wanxi, Wandong, Yudong, Xiangfan and other
places, smashing Kuomintang's defensive system in the Central
China Plains.
</P>
<P>
From September 1948 to January 1949, in accordance with
strategic arrangements of the CPC Central Committee and the
Central Commission, the PLA launched three decisive campaigns of
Liaoshen, Huaihai and Beiping-Tianjin, which eliminated the main
military strength on which Chiang Kai-shek relied for his
reactionary rule.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Asian Leaders Condole on Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of Pakistan and
Bangladesh and an Indian minister has sent condolences messages to
the Chinese leadership, mourning the death of Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping, who passed away in Beijing on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani President Farooq Leghari and Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif Thursday said that they had been "deeply grieved at the
passing away of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
In his message to Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Leghari
described Deng as "a great and revered statesman."
</P>
<P>
"He was the guiding light who steered his nation to the path of
reform, social justice and prosperity, " the Pakistani president
said, adding that Deng will be remembered as a trusted friend of
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
In a message to Chinese Premier Li Peng, the newly-elected
Pakistani prime minister Nawaz Sharif said, "We shall remember
Deng Xiaoping as a wise and able statesman whose enlightened
policies not only achieved laurels for the Chinese people but were
recognized the world over."
</P>
<P>
Sharif said that Deng's " contribution to regional and world
peace and stability has placed him amongst the great leaders of
modern history."
</P>
<P>
The Pakistan government has decided to hoist all flags in front
of the government buildings at half mast on February 20-25,
mourning Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi President Shahabuddin Ahmed and Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina expressed their deep condolences at the death of
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Shahabuddin Ahmed, in his message to Chinese President Jiang
Zemin, expressed his deep shock and great sorrow at the death of
Deng.
</P>
<P>
He said that China would enter the next millennium as a leading
world economic and political power by the guidance and vision of
late Deng's leadership.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hasina said in her message, "In his death the world has
lost an outstanding leader and a great visionary, who by his own
merit and quality of leadership, had earned for himself a
permanent place among the great leaders of modern history."
</P>
<P>
She said, Deng "was the successful architect of modern China.
He opened up China and completed its process of transition to a
leading world economic and political power that his great country
is today."
</P>
<P>
Indian External Affairs Minister I.K. Gujral, in his condolence
message, described Deng as a "colossus" who changed history and
contributed directly to building good relations between India and
China.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese leader's death would not halt the two countries'
move towards closer ties. Our relations have been moving in a
positive direction and to India's satisfaction," Gujral said.
</P>
<P>
The Indian minister said the people of India share the grief of
the people of China.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi Thursday
expressed condolences to the Chinese government and people over
Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
He said Malaysia acknowledged the vast contributions and
reforms made by the late Chinese leader to his nation.
</P>
<P>
Under Deng's leadership, Malaysia forged good relations with
China, which has been of mutual benefit, said the foreign
minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
