<HEADLINE> Melbourne Club Fined for Lack of Ground Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Australian soccer league club
South Melbourne was fined 7,500 dollars by Soccer Australia on
Friday for lack of ground security at last Sunday's home match
against Adelaide City, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Visiting player Angelo Costanzo had his eye cut by glass after
the match when South Melbourne fans threw rocks through the
windows of the bus after their side's 2-0 defeat, the reports
said.
</P>
<P>
Doctors were able to remove the glass from Costanzo's eye, but
he has been told he may not regain perfect sight, the reports
added.  
</P>
