<HEADLINE> Malaysian Political Leaders Mourn Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Ling Liong Sik, president
of the ruling Malaysian Chinese Association (MCA) and several
other party leaders today visited the Chinese embassy here to
express sorrow over the death of Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Those present on the occasion included the party's Deputy
President Lim Ah Lek, Secretary General Ting Chew Peh, Vice
President Chua Jui Meng, Youth chief Chan Kong Choy, Women Wing
leader Teng Gaik Kwan and Tan Chai Ho.
</P>
<P>
They signed the condolence book with words of Eternal
Remembrance of Comrade Deng Xiaoping written in Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters later, Ling Liong Sik who is transport
minister said Deng would be best remembered for the modernization
of China.
</P>
<P>
He credited Deng with the political stability in China which
had led to strong economic growth in the past decade.
</P>
<P>
The MCA is one of the ruling political parties in Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's Democratic Action Party (DAP) Secretary General Lim
Kit Siang and his 12-member delegation also visited the Chinese
embassy today their last respects to Deng.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Senate Chairman Mohamed Yaacob today also signed the
condolence book in the Chinese embassy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
