<HEADLINE> Seoul-Ho Chi Minh City Air Freight Route Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The first freight aircraft from
Seoul landed at Tan Son Nhat airport in Ho Chi Minh city on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The flight was conducted under a cooperation agreement on cargo
transportation between the Vietnam Airlines and Asiana Airlines of
 South Korea.
</P>
<P>
The Seoul-Ho Chi Minh City flight, using Boeing 767-300F, will
operate every Thursday with a freight capacity of 50 tons per
flight equally distributed to each airline. 
</P>
