<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French President Pays Tribute to Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 21 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
has paid his tribute to Deng Xiaoping who died in Beijing on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Deng "will remain in the memories as one of the greatest
figures of the history of China," Chirac said on Wednesday in his
condolence messages to Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Zhuo Lin,
the wife of Deng.
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping will remain in the history as the principal
artisan of the transformations that China has known over the past
20 years, which I could fully measure from my trips (to China) in
1978 and 1991," the French president said.
</P>
<P>
He said: "After having shown his qualities of strategy during
the years which preceded the founding of the People's Republic of
China, he imposed himself with his pragmatism and his vision for
the future, which allowed your country to engage in an
irreversible way on the road of opening and reforms."
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that France "received him on its soil with other
future (Chinese) leaders in the early 1920s " and it "received him
again, in an official way, half a century later, at the moment
when he was preparing with courage for the decisive revolvings" of
the history of China.
</P>
<P>
"His exceptional destiny led him to exercise the very high
responsibilities on the top of your country, which he has engaged
-- in less than one generation -- on the road of accelerated
modernization and an opening to the world without precedent," said
Chirac.
</P>
<P>
He said, "In this century, few men could have led such a vast
human community in changes which are as profound and as
determining as those which he did," he said.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping as vice premier paid an official visit to France
in 1975 when Chirac was French prime minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Killer Disease Threatens Animals in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, February 21 (Xinhua) -- While the severe drought
hitting most of the Somali towns and villages, the central region
of the country are particularly facing a serious unknown killer
disease which is mainly killing the goat and sheep.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the region said a new kind of sickness is being
seen by the herdsmen who said the sickness makes both the goats
and sheep stop drinking water, leak nose, develop a three-color
diarrhoea, high blood pressure, high fever before they died.
</P>
<P>
Veterinarians and environmentalists who are currently in the
region to assess the situation have assured that the disease is
neither anthrax nor trypanosomas which are common in the central
region of Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Lack of local laboratories made the doctors enable to diagnose
the type of the disease.
</P>
<P>
The doctors appealed to the international relief agencies to
provide necessary medical aid to the Horn of Africa country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
