<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 09:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Middle East Business Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The following are business
briefs from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Spain has offered 300 million U.S. dollars grant to
finance investment projects in Egypt over the coming three years.
</P>
<P>
Spain made the offer during a meeting between ministers of
trade of the two countries Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed to hold the first meeting of the
Egyptian-Spanish Joint Committee for Economy and Industry soon to
discuss means of boosting cooperation in various domains, an
Egyptian Gazettee report said.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Trade Minister Nawal el-Tatawi noted that the volume
of trade between the two countries reached 352.94 billion dollars
in 1995 against 206.38 billion dollars in 1992.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt has added 106 million feddans (44.52 million
hactares) to the agricultural patch since 1981, which in turn
greatly increased the staple crops self-sufficiency proportion.
</P>
<P>
While inaugurating the Egyptian Nutrition Society Symposium
activities starting recently, Minister of Agriculture and Land
Reclamation Youssef Wali was quoted by the Egyptian MENA news
agency as saying recently that the wheat sufficiency has risen
from 20 percent to 55 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Egypt has doubled its production of sugar and
achieved sufficiency in poultry during the past 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Now Egypt exports 450,000 tonnes of potatoes, more than
200,000 tonnes of other vegetables and 200,000 tonnes of citrus
fruits annually.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Oyak Renault Otomobil Fabrikalari A.S., Turkey's
major car producer, is to export 3,000 vehicles to Tunisia and
Egypt in 1997, company sources said here.
</P>
<P>
The Istanbul-based company has shipped its first 650 cars to
the two African countries, according to the local newspaper Daily
News.
</P>
<P>
Oyak Renault has exported 3,320 automobiles and spare parts to
Middle East, Central Asian , East European as well as African
countries, earning a total of 37.1 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The company, where the French automobile giant Renault has a
majority stake, aims to export 7,000 vehicles this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
