<HEADLINE> Deng Leaves Lasting Legacy for China: Kenyan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The policies initiated by
China's late leader Deng Xiaoping will remain in place, which is
"good for China", said a Kenyan newspaper, commenting on the
impact of Deng's passing away on China's future.
</P>
<P>
In an editorial entitled "Deng's Legacy May Keep China Going",
Daily Nation noted that the political leadership in China will
close ranks as the Chinese mourned Deng who passed away on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The paper pointed out that under Deng's guidance China
recorded a double-digit economic growth during the past dozen
years.
</P>
<P>
After Deng introduced his market-oriented economic reforms and
open-door policies, "the former sleeping giant stirred and awoke
-- and the world took notice," said the paper.
</P>
<P>
Deng should especially be credited with his "one country, two
systems" approach to Hong Kong which would remain its capitalist
system after returning to China on July 1, 1997 while Beijing
sticks to socialism.
</P>
<P>
Deng also pursued a policy of peaceful reunification with
Taiwan which is an integral part of China.
</P>
<P>
The paper stressed that growing prosperity of China is "Deng's
enduring legacy".
</P>
<P>
In a condolence message sent to Chinese President Jiang Zemin
on Thursday, Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi said economic
reforms and open-door policies initiated by Deng Xiaoping had
turned China into one of the world's fastest growing economies.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan leader pointed out that Deng's achievements will
continue to be admired by the world and will leave a lasting
legacy.
</P>
<P>
Moi noted that Deng will be remembered as a great leader who
served his country with dedication and commitment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
