<HEADLINE> Zairean Refugees in Zambia Want to Go Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Many Zairean refugees who
arrived in Zambia's Mpulungu Port via Lake Tanganyika said they
hoped to be taken back home instead of lodging in refugee centers.
</P>
<P>
Justin Mbayo, a former teacher who fled from Kamile, said it
was better to go back to Zaire than to sit and do nothing in the
refugee camp.
</P>
<P>
Lumbu Muyumba, who was former Kamile governor, preferred to be
transferred to Zaire's capital of Kinshasa, saying that most
members of his family are in Kinshasa except his wife, six
children and one grand daughter who are together with him in
Mpulungu.
</P>
<P>
However, some other refugees felt it would be safer to remain
in Zambia until the war in eastern Zaire is over. 
</P>
