<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets ASEAN Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People will carry
out the behest of Deng Xiaoping, the late leader of China, to
enhace the friendly cooperation with countries in the Asia-Pacific
region and in the world at large, said Qiao Shi, China's top
legislator.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC) Standing
Committee, made the remarks here today during his meeting with
members of the Beijing Committee of the Association of the
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
Mohamad Amia Jaafar, Malaysian ambassador to China and chairman
of the ASEAN Beijing Committee, on behalf of the governments and
peoples of ASEAN, expressed profound condolences over the death of
Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
He said that Deng made historical contributions not only to the
great cause of the Chinese people, but also to peace and stability
in the Asia-Pacific region, and to the international community.
</P>
<P>
Expressing thanks for Jaafar's statement, Qiao said that Deng
has devoted all his life to the Chinese people's cause of
liberation and socialist construction, and the Chinese people, who
are mourning over his death, will study his thought and push
forward China's socialist construction.
</P>
<P>
Deng has also made outstanding contributions to peace and
development in the Asia-Pacific region and in the world at large,
he added.
</P>
<P>
He stated that without Deng's outstanding leadership and his
theory on building socialism with Chinese characteristics, China,
the most populous country in the world, would not be able to
achieve today's successes in reform, opening-up and modernization.
</P>
<P>
Deng's theory will continue to be taken as the guidance over
China's development, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also spoke highly of China's friendly ties and cooperation
with ASEAN countries, as well as ASEAN's important role in
safeguarding peace and stability in the region, saying that China
and ASEAN have common interests and objectives in many aspects.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN Beijing Committee was established last September by
ambassadors to China of seven ASEAN countries. 
