<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Issues Decree to Encourage Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam today issued a decree
aimed at guaranteeing the implementation of a revised foreign
investment law in an effort to attract more foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
The decree, which consists of sub-law regulations, provides
guidelines for carrying out the new law in a transparent, specific
and practice manner, said the ministry of planning and investment
here.
</P>
<P>
The decree, coming into effect as from March 1, 1997, covers
procedures on land use, project design, environmental protection,
import procedures, registration for business operation and
banking, in 15 chapters with 104 articles.
</P>
<P>
The decree also deals with the decentralization and assignment
of issuance of investment licenses, and improvement of efficiency
of state management.
</P>
<P>
The law on foreign investment was promulgated nine years ago
and a revised law was adopted by the National Assembly last
November.
</P>
<P>
According to figures from the General Department of Statistics,
Vietnam has hitherto granted licenses to over 1,700 foreign
investment projects with a combined capital of over 27 billion
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
