end", will be remembered as the initiator of China's "open door"
policy which has taken China onto the development fast-track.
</P>
<P>
Rasmussen also said Deng will be remembered as one of China's
great leaders.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his sorrow over Deng's death, Norwegian Foreign
Secretary Egeland said Wednesday that Deng, as a statesman and
leader of the world's most populous nation, played a dominant role
in China's social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Egeland and Norwegian Prime Minister Thorjoern Jagland,
President of the Storting (Parliament) Kirsti Kolle Grondahl went
to the Chinese embassy in Oslo to pay their respects.
</P>
