<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Air Force Helps Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The Air Force of Zimbabwe has
deployed its two helicopter squadrons to evacuate flood victims
and airlift relief food to marooned people in both Zimbabwe and
Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
The air force headquarters in Harare said on Thursday their
Alouette III and Bell 412 helicopters had been deployed in
flooded regions near the Zambezi River catchment area while
another two Alouettes had been on a similar operation in
Mozambique since Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The air rescue missions have evacuated 137 people from the
flooded Zambezi River while delivering relief food.
</P>
<P>
Almost 200,000 people have been affected by the flood. People
who had settled in flood plains along the Zambezi River catchment
area are among the worst hit in both Zimbabwe and
Mozambique.
</P>
</TEXT>
