<HEADLINE> More Overseas-Backed Firms For East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, February 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
has approved 20,538 overseas-funded businesses, with contracts for
45.14 billion U.S. dollars in investment.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the sum of paid-in overseas
investment is 17.8 billion U.S. dollars, and 11,617
overseas-backed firms have begun operation or production.
</P>
<P>
While increasing efforts at improving the investment
environment, the province has also worked out preferential
policies to encourage investment in large projects since last
year, especially capital- and technology-intensive projects, a
move that has proven quite effective.
</P>
<P>
Last year alone, the province approved 1,987 overseas-funded
enterprises with 6.54 billion U.S. dollars of overseas funds
promised, and made use of 4.08 billion U.S. dollars of overseas
funds.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-backed enterprises also exported 5.82 billion
U.S. dollars worth of commodities in 1996, a rise of 21 percent
over the previous year and accounting for 58.2 percent of the
province's total exports.
</P>
<P>
These overseas-funded enterprises also generated 95.03 billion
yuan in industrial output value in 1996, a rise of 30 percent over
the previous year, and contributed 75.3 percent of the province's
newly-increased output value for the year, according to the
officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
