<HEADLINE> ESCAP Executive Secretary Mourns Deng's Demise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Adrianus Mooy, executive
secretary of the United Nations Economic and Social Commission for
Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP), has expressed a deep sense of sorrow
over the passing of Mr. Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
In a letter of condolence to Jin Guihua, Chinese ambassador to
Thailand, dated February 20, 1997, he said, "It is with a deep
sense of sorrow that I have learned of the demise of his
excellency Mr. Deng Xiaoping, paramount leader of China.
</P>
<P>
"His numerous contributions to the promotion of international
cooperation and understanding as well as to the development of
China and the welfare of her people have received universal
acclaim and will long be remembered.
</P>
<P>
"On behalf of my colleagues in the United Nations Economic and
Social Commission for Asia and the Pacific (ESCAP), and on my own
behalf, I wish to convey to you and through you to the government
and people of China our deepest sympathies and condolences on this
sad occasion."  
</P>
