<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
ended the week on a disappointing note with market index falling 1
percent. The market was affected by overnight fall on Wall Street
and higher local bond yields.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE-40 index ended 24 points lower at 2302 with a turnover
 of 51 million NZ dollars (35 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom was the big loser and accounted for half of the day's
turnover. Its share slided 25 cents to 6.60 dollars. The company's
lower third-quarter profit result announced on Tuesday contributed
 to the sharply weaker share price.
</P>
<P>
Among other leaders, Air New Zealand was down 1 to 2.79,
Brierley Investment dropped 1 to 1.35, Carter Holt Harvey rose 1
to 3.30, Fletcher Building was up 1 to 4.53 and Lion Nathan
dipped 1 to 3.58. 
</P>
