<HEADLINE> Russia Worried by "Unfriendly" War Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Russian Defense Minister Igor
Nikolayevich Rodionov Thursday condemned some European powers and
the United States for creating tensions among the former Soviet
Union Republics.
</P>
<P>
Rodionov told a news conference that some hostile powers from
the West were trying to worsen the Russian-Ukrainian relationship,
and this was threatening security in the Commonwealth of
Independent States.
</P>
<P>
He said a planned military exercises between the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization forces and Ukraine, which included a landing
exercise near the Russian-Ukraine border, was regarded by the
Russian government as not friendly.
</P>
<P>
The Russian defense minister pointed out that the involvement
in Afghanistan affairs by the U.S. and other powers was further
deteriorating Russia's southern border area.
</P>
<P>
Russia would not be indifferent to the fact that its state
security was being endangered, Rodionov said.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia was to send a delegation to Uzbekstan, one of
the former Soviet Union republics, to discuss security issues in
the south of the former Soviet Union. 
</P>
