<HEADLINE> 7 Kg of Gold Biscuits Seized in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 21 (Xinhua) -- In a major gold haul,
customs officials in Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala State of India,
seized 80 gold biscuits weighing seven kilograms from a Polish
national on Thursday, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The gold, worth about 100,000 US dollars, were seized at the
international airport of the southern Indian city.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old Polish national, identified as Wiatr Szymon
Stanislaw, had concealed the gold in the special cavities made in
the sole of his shoes.
</P>
<P>
Leaving Singapore on Wednesday, he came to Thiruvananthapuram
via Colombo, carrying the gold. 
</P>
