<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NZ PM Praises Deng as Architect of Modern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 21 (Xinhua) -- New Zealand Prime Minister
Jim Bolger has praised Deng Xiaoping as an architect of modern
China and a leader at the center of Chinese politics for more than
half a century.
</P>
<P>
In a media release issued after the death of Deng on Thursday,
Bolger said that Deng would be remembered first of all for the
role he had played in China's economic reform process. He
spearheaded China's opening to the outside world, and the
market-oriented policies that have since 1978 delivered China a
year-on-year growth rate of over 9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The release, available today, said New Zealand has benefited
from the success and stability of those policies. "And the whole
world is better off because China is engaged internationally, and
set to continue along the path. We have Deng to thank for that."
</P>
<P>
It continued that "to have achieved the advances he did, in a
country of 1.2 billion people, is a remarkable feat by anyone's
standards. Deng has laid a solid platform for the succeeding
generation of Chinese leadership to build upon."
</P>
<P>
Bolger expressed the deep sympathy of the NZ government and
people to the government and people of China in the loss of a
pre-eminent statesman and leader.  
</P>
</TEXT>
