<HEADLINE> Indonesian President Arrives in Yangon on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 21 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
arrived here today by special plane on a three-day state visit to
Myanmar at the invitation of Chairman of the State Law and Order
Restoration Council (SLORC) Senior-General Than Shwe.
</P>
<P>
The President's visit to Myanmar marked the final leg of his
tour to three Southeast Asian countries -- Cambodia, Laos and
Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
His visit is also the return visit to the one to Indonesia made
by Than Shwe in June 1995.
</P>
<P>
The President and his entourage including Foreign Minister Ali
Alatas were accorded a warm welcome at the Yangon International
Airport by SLORC Chairman Senior-General Than Shwe, Vice-Chairman
General Maung Aye, senior officials of the Myanmar Government as
well as foreign ambassadors to Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
During Soeharto's visit in Myanmar, talks on bilateral,
regional and international issues of common concern are expected
to be held with some bilateral agreements to be signed.  
</P>
