<HEADLINE> China And GM Joint Automobile Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 21 (Xinhua) -- China's Shanghai Automotive
Industry Corp. (Group) and the General Motors Corporation of the
United States are planning a jointly project to produce 100,000
Buick cars annually in Shanghai, the country's largest industrial
city.
</P>
<P>
The project involves an investment of 1.52 billion US dollars
from both sides to be built in Shanghai's Pudong Development Zone.
</P>
