<HEADLINE> African Hippo Gives Birth In South China Zoo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, February 21 (Xinhua) -- An African hippo yesterday gave
birth at a zoo in the southern island province of Hainan, after an
eight-month pregnancy.
</P>
<P>
The baby hippo reportedly weighs 16 kilograms and is 80
centimeters tall. Local sources say it is now in good condition,
but they said it was hard to tell its sex.
</P>
<P>
The mother hippo, whose name is Jia Jia, was brought from Japan
to the provincial zoo early last year, along with her mate Yuan
Yuan. Jia Jia was discovered to be pregnant after six months on
the island.
</P>
<P>
"She looked like she was in quite a bit of pain because it was
the first time for Jia Jia to give birth," said the zookeepers,
who noted that she kept rolling around in the water for more than
three hours during the labor.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the zoo has had some new baby animals
this year, such as black bears and dwarf horses. 
