<HEADLINE> East China Emphasizing Economic Efficiency For Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang
Province will make economic efficiency the central task for
developing foreign trade and economic cooperation this year.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with reporters, Yang Zucheng, director of the
Zhejiang Provincial Department of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, said that the province will make an effort to shift
from the practice of solely pursuing export and earnings quotas to
making efficiency as the central task of foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang will also strive to deal with the relations between
fairly large-scale and efficient management, to ensure continuous
development of foreign trade, and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
While improving understanding of this and trying to cultivate
100 major export commodities to adjust the province's economic,
especially the export, structure, the province will also work
harder to explore new overseas markets in addition to its
traditional markets.
</P>
<P>
The director also called for an emphasis on quality in the use
of overseas investment. Last year, the province did 13.386 billion
U.S. dollars worth of foreign trade, a rise of 16.1 percent over
the previous year. Of that amount, exports made up 9.334 billion
U.S. dollars, up 10.5 percent over the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
