<HEADLINE> Five Killed in Manila Suburb Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 21 (Xinhua) -- A fire razed a house at dawn
today in the eastern Manila suburbs, killing a Chinese-Filipino
couple and their three daughters, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police said Victor Tan, his wife Lydia and their kids were all
sleeping when trapped by the blaze inside their residence at
Makiling Street, Mandaluyong City.
</P>
<P>
Police said they suspected a foul play because the Tan's house
boy, who survived the conflagration, was outside the house when
the fire broke out.
</P>
<P>
But the house boy, Loreto Tatoy, alleged that he was drinking
beer inside a pub house, a few blocks away from Tan's house, when
the fire broke out. 
</P>
</TEXT>
