<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Applauds NATO-Russian Contacts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Security Secretary
Vladimir Gorbulin has said that his country supports NATO's
efforts to build closer ties with Russia.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with U.S. congressman Gerald Solomon on
Wednesday, Gorbulin said NATO and Moscow should set up a mechanism
for regular consultation, Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Solomon, heading a delegation of U.S. congressmen, arrived here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gorbulin said Ukraine backs a U.S. proposal to establish a
"Russia-NATO military structure," and believes joint military
maneuvers would build up confidence between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
"There will be no security in Europe without considering
Russia," he said.
</P>
<P>
Russia has strongly opposed plans by NATO to expand eastward to
take in countries from the now defunct Warsaw Pact, saying the
move would threaten its security.
</P>
<P>
To try to ease Russian fears, the U.S. has proposed the
creation of a joint NATO-Russian military brigade, mainly for
peacekeeping and has also offered a charter defining NATO-Russian
relations.
</P>
<P>
Russia has demanded a legally binding contract providing
security guarantees for Russia in the event of NATO's expansion.
</P>
<P>
Gorbulin announced that Ukraine hoped to sign a special
partnership agreement with NATO which he believed would provide
his country with security.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine has said in the past that it will not join the Western
military alliance and will keep its status as a non-aligned
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0270 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Biggest Orchid Plantation Built in Sichuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chengdu, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The world's largest orchid
nursery, designed to grow and protect the endangered Chinese
orchid, has been built in Pixian County in southwest China's
Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
Runde Orchid Park, with 10 million seedlings and covering an
area of more than 130 hectares, will become a large export center
of the rare flower.
</P>
<P>
With help from the Sichuan United University, the park has
carried out natural orchid production in large amounts. Scientists
from the university will also help build an orchid gene bank and
an orchid study center in the park.
</P>
<P>
Regarded by the Chinese as a symbol of virginity and nobility,
the sweet-smelling blossom has been grown in China for over 2000
years.
</P>
<P>
Chinese orchids are expensive; most are planted in small
numbers in family gardens, seldom entering the domestic and
overseas flower markets.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese orchid has large market potential in the world,
especially in Japan, the Republic of Korea and southeast
Asian countries, where the Chinese culture is prevalent.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the smuggling of Chinese orchids by some
foreigners has resulted in the loss of a large number of wild
orchids, and in some areas, known as homes for the flower, their
number is also shrinking.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0271 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 21 (Xinhua) -- All major Beijing-based
newspapers today mourned Comrade Deng Xiaoping who passed away
Wednesday night and carried Deng family's letter to Chinese
president Jiang Zemin and the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Various departments and institutions directly under the CPC
Central Committee yesterday eulogized Deng by reviewing his
glorious revolutionary career and great contributions to the
country, while all officials and employees of the central
government departments pledged to inherit Deng's legacy by
continuing to build socialism with Chinese characteristics and
performing their duties more conscientiously, the papers report.
</P>
<P>
Legislators attending a meeting of the Eighth Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), which opened
yesterday in Beijing, observed three minutes of silence before
beginning their discussions.
</P>
<P>
Staff workers of the NPC also convened a meeting to mourn Deng,
and said they will work diligently to prepare for the upcoming
Fifth Session of the Eighth NPC National Congress, which is
scheduled on March 1, according to the papers.
</P>
<P>
To illustrate Deng Xiaoping's lifelong pursuits and beliefs and
to perfectly close the last chapter of his life, Zhuo Lin, widow
of Deng, and their five children proposed in a letter to President
Jiang Zemin and the CPC Central Committee that no farewell
ceremony for Deng's remains be held and no ashes preserved. Deng's
ashes will be cast into the sea according to Deng's wish.
</P>
<P>
Zhuo and her children suggested that a memorial meeting be held
after the cremation. The casket containing Deng's ashes should be
covered by a flag of the CPC, with a color photo that displays
Deng's superb mental outlook above it.
</P>
<P>
Deng's corneas will be donated to an eyebank and his body be
dissected for the purpose of medical research, prior to the
cremation.
</P>
<P>
A picture of half-mast national flag at the Tiananmen Square
was also front paged by some major newspapers, including Guangming
Daily, Workers' Daily, and the Economic Daily.
</P>
<P>
On the international pages, major Beijing-based newspapers
carried condolences over Deng's death extended by top leaders of
the United Nations, the European Union, Russia, the United States,
Canada, France, India, Cuba, the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea, Viet Nam, the Republic of Korea, Germany, Japan, Spain, and
Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0272 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Nature Reserves To Be Doubled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 21 (Xinhua) -- The number of China's nature
reserves will be doubled to some 1,000 by around the year 2010,
according to the country's Vice-Minister of Forestry Wang Zhibao.
</P>
<P>
By then, there will be 100 national-level nature reserves,
around 40 percent more than at present, Wang said in an interview
with Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
"Starting from the 1950s, the establishment of China's nature
reserves has won much attention from the world, and a countrywide
network of the reserves has been formed," he said.
</P>
<P>
Such reserves throughout the country play an important role in
the protection of biological diversity, endangered species, and
the natural ecosystems in both China and the world, Wang stressed.
</P>
<P>
"The reserves of all kinds of forestry, wetlands and desert
ecosystems as well as the wildlife are important national
treasures that should be cherished forever," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the establishment of natural reserves has
contributed significantly to the protection of the giant panda.
</P>
<P>
"At the beginning of the next century, the reserves for the
giant panda will be exactly doubled to 28, basically covering the
whole area of its habitat," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0273 </DOCNO>
