<HEADLINE> Cuba, Canada Sign Tax Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Cuba and Canada signed a tax
cooperation agreement here Thursday marking the start of a series
of joint projects in economies, health, and education.
</P>
<P>
Under the document, a memorandum of understanding, Canada will
deliver financial aid of five million Canadian dollars (about 3.6
million U.S. dollars) in three years to the Cuba National Office
of Tax Administration.
</P>
<P>
The money will mainly go to the acquisition of information
equipment, technical assistance, and the training of Cuban
personnel.
</P>
<P>
The two countries had assumed a commitment last December on
social matters, especially health and education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
