<HEADLINE> Oremans Beats Second-Seeded Huber </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Miriam Oremans of the Netherlands
defeated second-seeded Anke Huber of Germany Thursday to enter the
quarterfinals of the Faber Grand Prix tennis tournament in
Hanover, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Oremans, 24, won the match 6-0, 7-5, 6-4 though, at the start
of the third set, her left thigh had to be treated on the
sideline, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Sabine Testud of France beat fifth-seeded
Brenda Schultz-McCarthy of the Netherlands 6-4, 6-3; Elena
Lichovtseva of Russia defeated Dominique van Roost of Belgium 6-1,
6-2, and Anne-Gaelle Sidot of France overcame Sabine Appelmans of
Belgium 6-3, 4-6, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
In the quarterfinals Friday, first-seeded Jana Novotna of the
Czech Republic will meet Lichovtseva, and sixth-seeded Barbara
Paulus of Austria plays Oremans.
</P>
<P>
Magdalena Maleeva of Bulgaria taks on Sandrine Testud of
France; and Sidot meets third-seeded Iva Majoli of Croatia.
</P>
