<HEADLINE> China to Sent Team for World Indoor Athletics Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 21 (Xinhua) -- China will send 20 athletes to
compete in the 6th world indoor athletics championships to be held
in Paris, France, from March 7 to 9.
</P>
<P>
The team includes Cai Weiyan and Sun Caiyun who improved the
world women's pole vault record many times, the Chinese Amateur
Athletics Association (CAAA) said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Li Meisu and Huang Zhihong, women's veteran shotput throwers,
will also participate in the biennial event.
</P>
<P>
The CAAA said all the participants were selected from the
Chinese national champions' athletics meet held last year. 
