<HEADLINE> Gebrselassie Sets 5,000 Meters Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Haile Gebrselassie of
Ethiopia broke his own 5,000 meters indoor world record by
finishing in 12 minutes 59.04 seconds at an international meeting
here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Meantime, the 23-year-old became the first man to run the
distance in less than 13 minutes indoors. His previous record was
13:10.98 set in Germany in January, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Gebrselassie, Olympic 10,000 meters gold medallist at Atlanta,
was also the world record holder for the outdoor 5,000 meters.
</P>
