<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Says No Cooperation With WTO on Row With EU on Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 20 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. said today that it
would not cooperate with the World Trade Organization (WTO) on
investigating the U.S.-EU dispute over Cuba, claiming the WTO is
not fit to referee such a row.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, U.S. Undersecretary of Commerce Stuart
Eizenstat expressed disappointment at the WTO's intervention into
its dispute with the European Union (EU) over sanctions against
Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The WTO announced earlier today that a dispute panel, made up
of three trade experts, was established to settle the disputes
between the U.S. and the EU. The panel is obliged to make a rule
within six months.
</P>
<P>
AT the center of the row is the U.S. Helms-Burton law, which
was enacted last year and aimed at curbing foreign investment in
Cuba. The EU argues it violates WTO principles.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. law has been under strong criticism worldwide since it
punishes not only the U.S. companys which trade with Cuba, but
also other countries.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and the EU had been in discussions, hoping to resolve
their differences before the WTO sets up a panel. The
establishment of the panel is automatic after their bilateral
direct talks failed to produce a settlement.
</P>
<P>
"The WTO is not an appropriate forum for resolving differences
over what is essentially a disagreement over foreign policy,"
Eizenstat affirmed.
</P>
<P>
"The United States wishes to provide every opportunity to
settle our differences with the EU in the dispute," added
Eizenstat.
</P>
<P>
But the official stressed that if no prompt agreement was
reached, the U.S. would tell the WTO that the organization's panel
has "no competence to proceed because it is a matter of U.S.
national security and foreign policy."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the EU also indicated that it remained its aim to
achieve a negotiated settlement through more bilateral discussions
despite the establishment of the WTO's panel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970221.0291 </DOCNO>
