<HEADLINE> Irish Company Develops Mad Cow Detection System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 20 (Xinhua) -- An Irish research company
announced in Dublin today that it has developed a new diagnostic
system, which can be used to detect mad cow disease, according to
press reports from Dublin.
</P>
<P>
Enfer Scientific Ltd said in a statement issued today that the
new detection system could be used to screen 1,000 beef carcasses
each day.
</P>
<P>
"The application of this technology can be expected to provide
a new public confidence amongst beef consumers and it will install
their detection system in any country or market," the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
Michael O'Connor, the company's technical director, said, "The
real significance of the test is that it can test a large number
of carcasses and get the results back before the meat enters the
human food chain."
</P>
<P>
Medical experts say that the current tests were based on actual
examination of brain tissue under a microscope. 
</P>
</TEXT>
