<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 20 (Xinhua) -- The New York stock market
fell for a second day today, under the pressure of profit-taking,
a weaker dollar and lower bond prices.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average lost 92.75 points today to
close at 6,927.38. But analysts said the market's run to a high of
7,067 Tuesday was overdone and that the recent drop was a
short-term setback.
</P>
<P>
The dollar fell sharply against the Japanese yen today, hurting
bond prices.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers on the New York Stock
Exchange, where volume was 490.24 million compared with 519.298
million Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock index was down 9.69 to 802.80
while the NYSE composite index fell 4.48 to 421.09.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite was down 18.18 to 1,347.40. The American
Stock Exchange market value index closed at 597.43, down 1.72.
