<HEADLINE> Egypt, PNA Initial Investment Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 20 (Xinhua) -- Egypt and the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) initialed this evening an agreement to
boost and protect investment between them, said the Egyptian MENA
news agency.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed to a thorough study of a draft
agreement regulating transport and transit trade between both
countries.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Minister of Economy, Foregin Trade and International
Cooperation Nawal al-Tatawi and PNA Minister of Planning and
International Cooperation Nabil Sha'ath signed the agreement and
the minutes of the joint Egyptian-Palestinian Committee on
Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have agreed to encourage businessmen and both
public and private sector institutions to invest in one another's
free industrial and trade zones.
</P>
<P>
The initialed accord also provides for the establishment of
joint Egyptian-Palestinian companies. 
</P>
